name: Mealmatch GmbH
about:
WE’LL CHANGE THE WAY PEOPLE MEET AND EAT FROM SCRATCH.

Mealmatch verbindet Menschen für ein gemeinsames Meal – in privater Umgebung und in Restaurants. 
So finden Teilnehmer neue Freunde in der Stadt und können im Urlaub und auf Geschäftsreisen mit netten Leuten lecker speisen.

Auf der neuen Online-Plattform und über die App kann sich jeder Volljährige kostenlos anmelden, um bei einem Meal neue Kontakte knüpfen oder als Gastgeber ein leckeres Meal kochen, dass er gerne mit anderen teilen möchte. 

Und das funktioniert ganz einfach.
Die angebotenen Meals beschreiben das Gericht, die Anzahl der möglichen Gäste, den Ort, das Datum und den Preis pro Gast. Interessierte Hungrige können dann in dem gewünschten Restaurant direkt über die Plattform einen Platz am offenen Tisch buchen und bezahlen oder bei privaten Gastgebern eine Anfrage zur Teilnahme verschicken. Der private Gastgeber entscheidet dann, ob er die Reservierungsanfragen von Gästen annehmen möchte oder nicht.

Für die Teilnahme an einem Meal erhält die Mealmatch GmbH eine Provision vom Gastbeitrag.
MEHR INFOS UND HIER EINFACH KOSTENLOS REGISTRIEREN: MEALMATCH.DE

name: Fincompare
about: FinCompare richtet sich an Kleine und Mittelständische Unternehmen (KMU) mit einem Finanzierungsbedarf ab 10.000 EUR. Über die Online-Plattform www.fincompare.de bietet FinCompare digitalen Zugang zu vielfältigen Finanzierungsmöglichkeiten. Unternehmen profitieren dabei – unabhängig und kostenlos – von einem Netzwerk von über 250 Finanzinstituten, darunter namhafte Geschäftsbanken, alternative Finanzdienstleister und innovative FinTechs. Der Prozess, der bislang intransparent, langsam und aufwändig war, wird mit FinCompare effizient, unabhängig und digital.

name: Nepos
about:
We are convinced that all people can use the Internet with full confidence in their ability. Therefore, we have taken on the responsibility of optimizing, transforming and curating digital services for the generation 65+. 

We are building a bridge between the elderly and the digital world.

Founded in 2015 by Paul Lunow and Florian Schindler, Nepos is evolving into the leading brand for technology for the elderly. Our goal is to enable everyone to participate in digital life. 

With the development of the world's simplest user interface for connecting the older members of our society, we succeeded in optimizing digital products and services for the current 65+ generation - from news and banking to navigation in the car. Nepos is backed by an international team with expertise in technical development, gerontology, neurology and usability design.

name: Zizoo
about:
Zizoo is the leading global boat rental platform. Zizoo helps sailors and curious travelers experience a boat holiday in a way that suits them. Whether its a romantic getaway at sea, a luxurious escape or a unique family holiday, Zizoo has the perfect boat for the right budget, With over 20,000 boats across locations in more than 35 countries to choose from, Zizoo is the number one destination for boat rentals in the world.


Who is Zizoo?

The Zizoo crew is made up of a dedicated team of professionals from digital marketing, business, development and the sailing industry. While our team members’ backgrounds vary across geographies and skills, the one thing we all have in common is our desire to help make lasting memories through providing unique boat holiday experiences.

name: Umanity
about: Umanity is a new human wellbeing app and live-streaming communications platform where people are introduced and matched around shared self-improvement interests for peer-group support.  Umanity’s B2B “data-insights” technology allows companies to recruit talent within our community by matching their needs with the soft skills and self-development accolades of users on our platform. In addition, corporates and startups alike will effectively nurture their culture and upskill existing employees through our Umanity VR training programs.

name: Elinvar
about: Elinvar is a WealthTech Platform as a Service, enabling asset & wealth managers to digitalize their business models. The multi-tenant platform offers service packages for core processes like client relationship management, online acquisition & coverage, onsite advisory support, portfolio management, reporting, invoicing, online client access and communication as well as third party connections, e.g. to custodian banks, market data or KYC providers. Elinvar’s partners profit from the combination of leading technology and the optimal regulatory setup as Elinvar holds all necessary BaFin licenses. With this comprehensive approach, Elinvar creates the unique opportunity for its partners to execute new business models, to access new value chains and to optimize their costs. As all partners in the ecosystem combine their core competencies, together they generate maximum customer value. The best solutions arise through partnership.

name: Penta
about: Penta is the digital platform for business banking aimed at SMEs and startups. We are on the mission to disrupt business banking in Europe and worldwide. Our vision is to build a platform of connected services around a bank account which would allow business owners to use one platform for all their financial needs. Penta is designed to let business owners save time and money on banking so that they can focus more on their core business.  Today, Penta offers more features than traditional banks, such as the ability to get multiple business cards per company, digital expense management, low foreign transfer rates, fast online support in English & German, flexible pricing, and more. The account can be opened online in minutes via our website - www.getpenta.com.  Penta’s story begins with stories of deep frustrations among bank users. Our founders, all serial entrepreneurs, many times had terrible experiences with their business banks. In February 2016, they happened to discuss the issue with a group of fellow entrepreneurs and soon after they set out on a journey to create the most advanced bank for SMEs. Penta launched in Germany in January 2018 and raised over 8 Mio. EUR in August 2019, in an investment round (series A) led by HV Holtzbrinck Ventures. In March 2020 Penta closed its series B and raised 18.5 Mio. Euro with existing investors HV Holtzbrinck and finleap as well as new investors RTP Global, ABN AMRO Ventures and VR-Ventures.    Questions? Email us at hello@getpenta.com Follow us on Twitter! http://twitter.com/getpenta

name: cloudeo
about: cloudeo operates a unique, vendor independent, data agnostic market platform through which customers can obtain professional geoinformation services from leading national and international providers at low cost. Services include dedicated solutions for many industries; such as agriculture, urban and landscape planning, logistics, telecommunications, and water management. Customers are provided with high resolution imagery, 3D terrain models, thematic maps, and sensor data for a wide range of applications. All of which can be combined with a large selection of software packages, analytics and IT that facilitate the processing of these data. cloudeo makes it easy for partners to enter the market on a local, national or international basis. Our cloud-based platform empowers new business models while enabling production automation, delivery, and administration. For these reasons it is cost-effective, transparent and reliable.

name: KEWAZO GmbH
about:
KEWAZO is digitizing construction with robotics and data analytics. We integrate robotic platforms on-site to enable digital services. In scaffolding, our robotic material hoist LIFTBOT saves up to 44% of labor costs, addresses labor shortage, and improves safety. By having our robots on-site, we collect operational data and provide it to our customers in the form of a data analytics platform, enabling more proactive management of both individual projects and companies overall. As the next step, the robotic system will be adjusted for material transport in other construction trades and industrial applications.

Find us on facebook: www.facebook.com/kewazo
Follow us on twitter: https://twitter.com/KewazoRobotics

name: Alcandia Travel
about:
Our vision is to create a whole new travel experience, starting from the consumer's first travel desire, first contact and individual advisory through travel agencies, improved existing infrastructure to the final point of cutting-edge technological progress to take today's market standards to the next level.

We develop harmonized solutions for hundreds of isolated applications in the travel market to serve tour operators, travel agencies, and above all the customer.

We strive to take travel forward by new and revolutionary technology, both nationally and internationally.

We are constantly looking for support and talented people. If you are interested in working in a startup environment and if you are passionate about travel, get in touch with us!

name: Sensorberg
about:
Imprint: https://www.sensorberg.com/imprint

Sensorberg digitizes buildings and turns lifeless concrete bodies into digital worlds of experience that make our lives and our work much easier. Even more: a real experience. Through digitalization, it is possible to get even closer to the customer and to represent his needs even more precisely through appropriate offers. Using smartphones, users can enter a building without a card or key, operate elevators, book meeting rooms at short notice or adjust the room temperature to suit their needs. Smart home or office technology from Sensorberg makes this possible - in a very direct way.

Taking access to the building as a starting point, interactive solutions extend to include meeting room reservations and employee/visitor management. Sensorberg takes a clear focus on simplicity, transparency and user experience. The solution is available for both outfitting new building constructions and retrofitting existing infrastructures.

Sensorberg is a Berlin-based technology company founded in 2013. Sensorberg employs about 30 workers and is headquartered in Berlin. Stefan Scheuerle is the CEO.

name: Ordercube
about:
We aspire to change the restaurant experience for everybody. What if there was a device that could bridge the communication gap between guests and waiters, support restaurateurs and serve as an atmospheric light gadget?

The Ordercube is the idea to simplify communication in restaurants. The illuminated cube made from acrylic glass and powered by rechargeable batteries replaces the candle on every table. When the guest is willing to be served, the cube can be activated via touch sensor. This allows the waiter to see, if patrons want to order or pay, and in which order. Furthermore, the Ordercube can be operated via app for additional overview. Thus customer complaints about bad service are a thing of the past.

name: reBuy
about:
reBuy’s mission is to provide a conscious, low-cost alternative to new products, without compromising in looks or functionality. We developed a unique refurbishing process that upgrades pre-owned products & increases their value. 

The journey started with university students, a small shelf full of video games & a big vision. Since then, reBuy has grown into a 10.000 m² warehouse and logistic center, has more than 550 employees and has had 5 million customers, making reBuy the lead player in Europe.

name: TowerPower
about: TowerPower is combining solar photovoltaics, smart energy storage, and software intelligence to shift telecommunications towers away from expensive and polluting diesel generators.

name: Corebook
about: An online brand guidelines platform to develop & maintain brand design integrity for the world's most brilliant brands and their creators. Sign up & try for free at corebook.io

name: Oriient
about:
Oriient provides the first GPS-like service indoors.

Hyper accurate Indoor Location Awareness, without the hassle.
You don't need to install anything, you don't need to maintain anything.
It's like GPS - a service you simply use.

Whether you operate a mall, megastore, hospital, university or an office building, your visitors and staff expect the place to be convenient, accessible and friendly.
It is what they have online, and it is what they expect offline.
We can help you achieve that, without any hardware installation or maintenance.

name: Qover
about: We are Qover, we rock the status quo of insurance.   We build our own insurance products and make them available in real-time through open API's. Any digital business model can embed or sell our products within minutes. Frictionless, transparent and relevant at the right moment.   As tech pioneers we execute hard and fast to build the new insurance stack for the Digital Revolution.   Ninja’s get **it done. One dream, One team.   #HackingInsurance

name: FourKites
about:
FourKites is the world's fastest-growing predictive supply chain platform, delivering real-time visibility and execution for Fortune 500 companies and third-party logistics firms across 70 countries. Using a proprietary algorithm to calculate shipment arrival times, FourKites enables customers to lower operating costs, improve on-time performance, and strengthen end-customer relationships. With a network of more than four million GPS/ELD devices, FourKites covers all modes including ocean, rail, parcel and over-the-road. The platform is optimized for mobile and equipped with market-leading end-to-end security. 

To learn more, visit www.fourkites.com.

name: Devisenwerk
about:
Devisengeschäfte einfach, schnell und sicher tätigen

Devisenwerk steht für eine effiziente und günstige Abwicklung Ihrer Transaktionen. Wir kümmern uns um den Tausch der Devisen und eine sichere Ausführung der internationalen Zahlungen. Sie legen in wenigen Klicks fest welcher Betrag wohin überwiesen werden soll und zahlen den Gegenwert ein. Devisenwerk veranlasst alle weiteren Schritte und garantiert höchste Sicherheit.

Devisenwerk erleichtert Ihnen auch die Verwaltung Ihrer Devisentransaktionen. Über Ihr persönliches Dashboard – Ihren Account – können Sie die Ausführung von Überweisungen in Echtzeit bis zum Empfänger mit verfolgen. Außerdem finden Sie dort eine Übersicht aller Devisengeschäfte, die Sie über Devisenwerk abgewickelt haben.

name: mentavio
about:
mentavio is one of the largest marketplaces for online counselling, coaching and psychotherapy via webcam, instant messaging, secure onsite e-mail in Germany, Austria, Switzerland and the Spanish speaking countries. More than 350 licensed psychologists, psychotherapists, alternative practitioners for psychotherapy and coaches currently present themselves on www.mentavio.com and www.mentavio.es and offer clients and patients the opportunity to receive fast, discreet, location-independent and high quality counselling. 
 
mentavio is operated by arztkonsultation ak GmbH, Schwerin.

name: Sureify
about:
Sureify is a SaaS platform for Life and Annuity companies around the globe. Sureify’s sales, customer self-service engagement solution, and their up-sell cross-sell solutions enable life insurers to connect, service, and sell to their new and existing customers using the most life insurance focused platform in the market today. The enterprise platform solution is secure, scalable, and delivers pragmatic features with the basics of the everyday digital life insurer front of mind.

The Sureify solution encompasses the consumer-facing web and mobile applications, automated messaging and self-service platform, agent engagement console, marketing dashboard, underwriters data platform with analytics and reporting for executive overview. Sureify also can be implemented right on top of existing core systems and CRM systems while integrating with existing contact center platforms, customer apps, and most life insurance emerging and traditional 3rd party applications. All this is supported by Sureify’s Customer Experience team to ensure best practices, ideation, configuration both inside enterprise and end-user digitalization.

Life insurers use the Sureify platform for direct and agent digital sales, policyholder service and self-service, new product education and marketing, churn reduction, upsell cross-sell, and complete digital tracking of policyholders. The time is now for the life and annuity insurer.

name: Promo Pads
about: Promo Pads (www.promo-pads.com)

name: Datarella
about:
INDUSTRIAL BLOCKCHAIN SOLUTIONS

Datarella is a Big Data and Blockchain solutions provider.

MISSION STATEMENT
Datarella delivers data-driven solutions -everything you need for digital business transformation and Big Data: Cloud storage and computing, machine learning (AI) and predictive analytics. Datarella Blockchain Solutions is your full service consulting and development for business applications of the blockchain. Datarella IoT Solutions provide data driven business logic for connected devices and the industrial internet.

BLOCKCHAIN SOLUTIONS
Datarella Blockchain Solutions is the full service consulting and development agency for your blockchain project. Datarella delivers all things blockchain: from workshops and trainings to solutions architecture, application development and hosting of blockchain technology – everything you need for your Proof of Concept.

Datarella CodeLegit provides the legal framework for smart contracts on the blockchain – to close the gap between code and law.
Datarella serves clients over many industries: Insurance, automotive, manufacturing, media, politics and government.

BIG DATA SOLUTIONS
Datarella delivers Big Data Solutions – all you need for digital business transformation and Big Data: Cloud storage and computing, the complete data science portfolio of machine learning and predictive analytics, workshops and trainings, application design, data driven user experience, big data architecture and hosting of big data systems.

Datarella IoT Solutions provide data driven business logic for connected devices and the industrial internet.
Datarella serves clients over many industries: Insurance, automotive, manufacturing, media, politics and government.

name: Dr Omnibus
about:
DrOmnibus (www.dromnibus.com) is MedTech company, the very first European company which has joined a Launchpad Accelerator in Google San Francisco, a team of experts with long-standing experience in therapy and new technologies. 

DrOmnibus develops the ABA DrOmnibus app, focusing on resources for ABA therapy. The app is not just another data collection system but something more - it combines resources, ABA programs with real-time data collection, reports after each session and support for cooperation with parents. 

ABA DrOmnibus app can support early intervention for children with ASD, giving access to personalized, safe methods based on ABA. It can also be a supplementary tool for home therapy. For parents, we offer the ABA DrOmnibus for Parents version that is complementary with ABA DrOmnibus Pro.

Awards:

name: XTAL
about:
XTAL is invested and founded by a Hong Kong private investor and industry veterans in semiconductor design and manufacturing field. Our company is located in Silicon Valley, a centre of technology, innovation and entrepreneurship.

Our core team members consist of well-seasoned experts in EDA (Electrical Design Automation), IC design, manufacture and capital equipment capacity. We take pride in specializing in yield enhancement, software optimization and hardware implementation targeting semiconductor ecosystem. Our winning-streak track record in solving multi-complex problems in the arena of design optimization and yield improvement helps us engage seamlessly with top IC designers, manufacturers and semiconductor capital equipment companies around the globe. We also offer extended consulting services to the industry.

name: ThinxNet
about:
ryd is a fast growing IoT / FinTech start-up from Munich. Founded in 2014, ryd puts the digital future on the road. ryd is a connected car platform focusing on ryd pay and ryd box. ryd pay is the largest cross-brand solution for mobile payments directly at the gas pump. The ryd box, an OBD2 connector, turns every car into a SmartCar. ryd makes driving better and more comfortable, whether at the gas station, for individuals and connected company fleets or as an innovative telematics solution for insurers.

Partnering with Mastercard and Daimler AG in 2020 and joining forces with AXA Switzerland, we are onto a great momentum to change mobility and payment of the future.

ryd pay is a European ecosystem. With ryd pay, payment is made directly via app at the fuel pump or in the car. Therefore, going into the petrol station shop becomes unnecessary. In addition to our own ryd app as a direct channel, we enable third parties such as navigation apps, in-car payment from car manufacturers or apps to use the pay@pump features via an API or SDK implementation. Our vision is to be exactly where the digital customer of our partners is.

Currently ryd is available in Germany, Austria and Switzerland and is preparing the Go-Live in Portugal, Spain, Benelux and the rest of Europe.

Abonnieren Es ist wirklich schön, dass eine deutsche Firma so guten Service anbietet!Ich würde jederzeit gern wieder mit Gastrozentrale zusammenarbeiten! Kunde: Andres Carvajal, TAQUERIA Alle bezogenen Produkte haben genau unseren Anforderungen entsprochenund sind innerhalb kürzester Zeit bei uns eingetroffen. Kunde: Dominik Kraetz, Patisserie Isabella Hilfsbereit und zuvorkommend. Vielen Dank für den tollen Service! Kunde: Gesa Stockburger, Diginet Unsere Referenzen Gastronomiebedarf günstig im Gastro Online Shop kaufen Gastronomiebedarf Gastronomiebedarf / Hotelbedarf - endlich Alles an einem Ort! Gastrozentrale.de ist Deutschlands große Beschaffungsplattform für Großküchentechnik und Gastronomiebedarf / Hotelbedarf. Wir bieten die Anlaufstelle für alle, die auf der Suche nach hochwertiger Gastronomieeinrichtung sind und einen Full-Service gerne in Anspruch nehmen. Ob Getränketheke, Pizzaöfen, Flaschenkühler oder Dampfgarer, bei uns finden Sie alles für die Einrichtung von Bars, Cafés und Restaurantbetrieben  die besten Marken, die neueste Technik, schnell geliefert und zum fairen Preis. Neben unserem Bestsellersortiment bieten wir auch immer wieder Rabatte und Sonderaktionen in unserem Newsletter und in den sozialen Medien an. Von A wie Aufschnittmaschine über P wie Pizzaofen bis Z wie Zahnstocher Auf Gastrozentrale.de finden Sie über 50.000 Artikel, von Großküchentechnik über wie z.B. Gewerbekühlschränke und Konvektomaten bis hin zu Kleingeräte für die professionelle Gastronomie wie Pattyformer und Porzellangeschirr. Natürlich haben wir auch sonstigen Gastronomiebedarf des täglichen Gebrauchs im Angebot. Gemäß unserem Motto Finde schnell was du brauchst haben wir unseren Online-Shop übersichtlich strukturiert. Wählen Sie die Hauptkategorie in der oberen Navigation und schon erhalten Sie eine Auswahl weiterer Unterkategorien. In der Kategorie Kühltechnik finden Sie z.B. die Unterkategorien: Gewerbekühlschränke, Kühltheken, Kühlregale oder Kühlvitrinen. Schließlich wollen Sie als Kunde bei der Suche Zeit und Geld sparen! Wir machen ernst mit Kundenzufriedenheit Apropos Kunde: Sie betreiben ein Restaurant, ein Hotel, einen Imbiss oder müssen in einem Unternehmen eine gewerbliche Küche einrichten? Dann kennen Sie sicher auch die Tatsache, wie oft neuer Gastronomiebedarf gebraucht wird - und dass die laufenden Investitionen oft schnell ins Geld gehen können. Guter Rat ist hier oft teuer. Welcher Hersteller von Gaststättenbedarf ist der richtige, wie kann man an günstigere Preise herankommen, und das am Besten noch mit solider, professioneller Beratung von einem fachkundigen Partner? Sie wollen zum Beispiel eine Cocktailbar einrichten und brauchen einen Eiswürfelbereiter, einen Getränkekühlschrank und entsprechenden Barbedarf. Oder Sie suchen einen Pizzaofen und sind verunsichert ob der großen Preisunterschiede? Ihr lokaler Händler hat nur alte Geräte herumstehen, oder eine zu kleine Auswahl - im Internet dagegen sehen Sie nur einen Haufen bunte Bilder und wissen nicht, auf welche Qualitätsmerkmale Sie achten sollen. Zentralisieren Sie Ihren Einkauf mit Gastrozentrale Hier kommt Gastrozentrale ins Spiel. Wir kommen vom Fach und richten seit über 30 Jahren gewerbliche Küchen, Bars, Diskotheken und Gaststätten ein. So haben wir entsprechende Fachleute für Großküchentechnik und Edelstahlmöbel, Gläser, Hotelporzellan und gedeckten Tisch, aber auch für die neuesten Trends in der Gastronomie wie Sous-Vide Cooking, BBQ Grills und Smoker, die auch dem härtesten Restaurantbetrieb standhalten. Mit der richtigen Beratung kann man hier nicht nur die geeigneten Hersteller und Produkte finden, (sondern auch eine Menge Geld sparen). Und das nicht nur beim Einkauf selbst, sondern auch bei der Montage und Installation der Großküchengeräte, sowie - Achtung auf die diversen Verordnungen - bei der Genehmigung und Abnahme der Geräte. Gastronomiebedarf ist also ein weites Feld. (Und, Hand auf's Herz: mit uns behalten Sie die Übersicht). Vom Zahnstocher über Speisekarten und Geschirr bis zu Produkten für Kochtechnik und Küchenabluft vertreibt Gastrozentrale on- und offline über 120.000 Produkte von mehr als 500 weltweiten Herstellern. Dadurch, dass wir schon lange in der Großküchenbedarf-Branche agieren, können wir hier nicht nur auf gute Beratung, sondern auch auf exzellente Einkaufskonditionen zurückgreifen. Die Suche hat ein Ende - sparen Sie mit uns echtes Geld Und, wichtig zu wissen: Wenn Sie dennoch etwas günstiger gefunden haben, greift im Zweifelsfall auch unsere Bestpreisgarantie. Doch achten Sie darauf: Nur weil die von Ihnen gesuchten Gegenstände in Küchen verwendet werden können, ist es nicht gleich echter Großküchenbedarf! Für die Gastro gibt es nicht nur spezielle Kleinteile und Artikel wie Tischwäsche, Speisekarten, Chafing Dishes oder natürlich die professionellen Geräte der Großküchentechnik - auch bei Servietten, Geschirr, Gastromöbel und Gläsern sollten Sie darauf achten, dass nur echter Gastrobedarf erworben wird - am Besten mit entsprechender Beratung von Gastrozentrale. Der erste Grund: in der Gastronomie und in Großküchen werden auch "einfache" Artikel wie Teller, Kochmesser, Tischwäsche, Besteck, aber auch Möbel viel stärker beansprucht und müssen auch unter stressigen Konditionen standhalten. Mehr als ein Online-Shop für Gastronomiebedarf Zweitens müssen die Gegenstände lange vorrätig sein und am Besten über eine Nachkaufgarantie verfügen, schließlich wollen Ihr Koch und Ihre Gäste die gewohnte Qualität beibehalten. Drittens gibt es massive Qualitätsunterschiede zwischen einzelnen Herstellern, die je nach Einsatzzweck günstig - oder ungeeignet sind. Wenn Sie zum Beispiel einen Bratwurststand oder einen Dönergrill besitzen, werden Sie wahrscheinlich auf Plastikgeschirr und Einwegbesteck zurückgreifen können. Wenn Sie Betreiber einer Showküche oder eines Hotelrestaurants sind, brauchen Sie qualitativ hochwertigen Gastronomiebedarf, der auch vor dem Gast einen guten Eindruck macht. Die Kunst der richtigen Produktauswahl steckt hier oft im Detail. Dürfen im Bereich Barausstattung Ihre Ausgießer aus Plastik sein, und können sie auch zähflüssige Liköre ausgießen? Sind die Longdrink-Gläser für Ihre Diskothek auch bruchfest und vertragen robuste Handhabung? Ist das Einweggeschirr für Ihren Catering-Event biologisch abbaubar, hitze- und feuchtigkeitsbeständig sowie geschmacksneutral? Ist die Eiswürfelmaschine besser Luft-, oder Wasser-gekühlt? Vertragen Ihre Gastro-Möbel auch abenteuerlustige Kinder und nassen Fußboden? Am besten, Sie reden mit echten Profis - mit unserem Team bei Gastrozentrale. Bei uns beraten nur echte Experten Unsere Gastronomieexperten haben jahrelange Erfahrung als Koch, Catering-Unternehmer, Hotelfachmann und Gastrofachberater gesammelt und beraten Sie kostenlos und unverbindlich zum Thema Großküchentechnik und Gastronomiebedarf. Ob Kühltheke, Fleischwolf, Pattyformer, Pizzateller, Edelstahlmöbel oder ausgefallene Speisekarte: Egal welche Produkte Sie suchen, wir finden genau das, was Sie brauchen, und das zum günstigen Preis mit dem richtigen Service. Testen Sie uns und besuchen Sie heute noch unseren Online-Shop. Und sollten Sie einmal nicht das finden, was Sie brauchen, sprechen Sie mit einem unserer Berater. Wir freuen uns auf Sie! Großküchenplanung Großküchenplanung und Gastronomieberatung - wir bauen Ihren Laden, und helfen Ihnen beim Wachsen! Wussten Sie schon? Gastrozentrale ist nicht nur ein Großküchen-Shop - als echter Gastro-Dienstleister entwerfen und gestalten auch Ihre ganz individuellen gastronomischen Träume, und das mit mehr als dreißig Jahren Erfahrung in der Branche (mehr dazu auch in unserem Firmenportrait). Von der Neuplanung oder dem Umbau von Gastronomieküchen / Hotelküchen über die Gestaltung oder Renovierung des Gastraums bis hin zur fertigen Szene-Bar oder Ihrem ersten, eigenen Franchising-System - wir stehen Ihnen zu Seite! Dabei legen wir nicht nur Wert auf eine konzeptionell wie handwerklich exzellente CAD-Planung und eine Kücheneinrichtung mit guten Preis-/ Leistungverhältnis - wir sehen auch Ihr Projekt stets als Ganzes, hinter dem viele Erwartungen - und Risiken! - seiner Auftraggeber stehen. Daher beraten wir Sie gerne auf Wunsch auch zusätzlich von der Konzeptoptimierung über die Budget- und Küchenplanung bis hin zur Einkaufsoptimierung sowie der Finanzierung und Expansion Ihres Vorhabens  (bis Sie wirklich zufrieden sind). Unsere Erfahrung mit Großküchen: Zuverlässigkeit, Einsatz und immer eine Idee mehr. Ob Cook-and-Serve, Cook-and-Chill oder als Zentralküche mit anschließender Speisenvakuumierung und -frostung. Wir kennen die Anforderungen an moderne, gewerbliche Gastro-Küchen aus Individualgastronomie, Hotellerie und Gemeinschaftsverpflegung. Stets auf dem neuesten Stand der Technik, aber mit einem gesunden unternehmerischen Blick auf Ihren Geldbeutel helfen wir Ihnen, aus einer Örtlichkeit und Ihrem Budget das Beste herauszuholen. Gemeinsam mit Ihnen und einem industrieerfahrenen Dienstleister-Team gehen wir auf die örtlichen Gegebenheiten ein, schätzen und unterstützen bauliche Veränderungen und helfen Ihnen bei der finalen Realisierung Ihres gastronomischen Vorhabens. Dabei beachten und optimieren wir nicht nur die Raumaufteilung sowie Laufwege in Küche, Lager und Speisenausgabe, sondern legen auch großen Wert auf neueste Energiekonzepte und wirtschaftliche Nachhaltigkeit. Und sollten Sie einmal ein ausgefallenes, aber dennoch vielversprechendes Konzept verfolgen - wir gehen gern die Extrameile und beschaffen genau das, was Sie für Ihren Traum benötigen: Nudelmaschinen aus Japan, BBQ-Smoker aus Texas sowie Tantuni-Stationen aus Marokko. (Durch unser internationales Investoren-Netzwerk und unsere Erfahrung bei Förderbanken können wir nebenbei dem ein oder anderen Projekt auch zu größerer finanzieller Stärke verhelfen.) Unser Leistungsspektrum im Überblick: 1. Gastronomieberatung im Bereich Konzepte und Vorhabenplanung Quick-Check und Konzeptanalyse, ob als direkter Berater der Geschäftsführung oder als ausführender Dienstleister Konzeptoptimierung und 100 Punkte Plan Logoentwurf und Mood-Board Gestaltung inkl. Konzepte für Farb- und Materialspektrum Produktauswahl und Innenraumplanung, gerne auch in 3D-Visualisierung Menüoptimierung und Food-Produktenwicklung Beschaffungsberatung Food/Non-Food und Einkaufsoptimierung Permanente Unterstützung bei der Umsetzung 2. Großküchenplanung (alle Leistungsphasen) als professionelle Planungsgesellschaft Grundlagenermittlung, auch anhand von Referenzen und Skizzen Standortanalyse oder Umbau-Analyse Auswahl der richtigen Großküchentechnik Vorplanung der Großkücheneinrichtung Entwurfsplanung in 3D CAD und Visualisierung Genehmigungsplanung Ausführungsplanung als Fachplaner Objekt-/ Bauüberwachung bis zur Montage Objektbetreuung aller Großküchen als unterstützender Dienstleister 3. Finanzierungs- und Betriebsberatung (Optional) Erstellung eines Finanzplans und einer Projekt-Timeline, z.B. für Neugründung oder Umbau Hilfe bei der Erstellung eines Businessplans und der GmbH-Gründung Unterstützung bei der Auswahl und Ansprache geeigneter Finanzierungspartner Kostenanalyse und Verbesserung von Einparpotenzialen Unterstützung bei der Personalakquise Übersicht im Verordnungsdschungel - dank unserer Gastrozentrale-Experten Auf einen Auftraggeber und Bauherren in der Großküchenplanung, als auch auf uns als Dienstleister kommen heutzutage eine Menge Regeln zu: HACCP-Hygienebestimmungen, Richtlinien bei der Lebensmittelverordnung, Europäische Gesetzgebungen bei Mensen und Betriebscasinos, Arbeitsstätten-Vorgaben und Baunormen für Hotellerie, Kühlkettenverordnungen in Schulmensen und der Gemeinschaftsverpflegung, Ergonomische Aspekte bei der Bargestaltung, Vergabekriterien bei der Planung und Ausschreibung, Richtlinien bei Sanitär und Lüftung - und manches mehr. Dank unserer In-House Dienstleister und des Gastrozentrale-Expertennetzwerks kein Problem! Wir kennen die Tücken der offiziellen Normen für Großküchentechnik und helfen Ihnen gleich zu Beginn Ihres Projektes, Kollisionen mit örtlichen und bundesweiten Gesetzgebungen zu vermeiden. Mit unseren Checklisten und Praxis-Tipps geben wir Ihnen vor und während der Projektzeit auch Instrumente an die Hand, Ihrem Vorhaben zum Erfolg zu verhelfen. Unser Repertoire als Dienstleister in der Großküchentechnik: Vom Szeneclub bis hin zur Hotelküche Es gibt wohl kaum einen Küchentypus, mit dem wir als Planer und Berater für die Gastro nicht schon Erfahrung gemacht hätten. Dabei machen wir oft die Erfahrung, dass einzelne Gastronomie-Kategorien immer stärker verschmelzen. Auch Kantinen von Großunternehmen wollen heute gutes Design und gesundes, trendiges Essen anbieten, Sterneläden bieten plötzlich Take-Away an, und Szene-Gastronomen wiederum sind froh, bei Arbeitsabläufen und HACCP-Hygienekonzepten auf unsere Erfahrungen aus der Betriebsgastronomie zurückgreifen zu können. Egal ob Dönergrill oder Hotelbar - die Ansprüche der Gäste sind höher geworden: gesundes Essen, Drinks mit "Signatur" und Licht- bzw. Raumkonzepte, bei der Ernährung, Freizeit und soziales Erlebnis miteinander verschmelzen. Dabei spielen auch allgemeine, gesellschaftliche Trends eine Rolle, z.B. Müllvermeidung, regionaler Bezug oder kreativ-frecher Umgang mit verschiedenen ethnischen Herkünften. Doch keine Sorge: Wir von Gastrozentrale leben nicht in einem "Elfenbeinturm" der technischen Großküchenplanung: wir sprechen täglich mit Meinungsmachern und Trendsettern in der Gastronomie, bilden uns und unsere Mitarbeiter ständig fort und arbeiten bei kniffligen Fragen auch mit renommierten Spezialisten zusammen. Unser Motto "die Gastroexperten" heißt nämlich auch, dass Gastronomie immer auch Gemeinschaftsleistung ist. Nur gemeinsam mit unseren Mitarbeitern, und nur zusammen mit Ihnen können wir zur Höchstform auflaufen. Die folgende Liste gibt Ihnen einen Überblick über die Verpflegungs- und Küchen-Konzepte, in denen wir diese Gemeinschaftsleistung schon erbracht haben. Kantinen Betriebsgastronomie Altenheimküchen Mensen Schulverpflegung Hotels Krankenhausverpflegung Traditions- und Sport-Gaststätten Erlebnisgastronomie Szenegastronomie Catering Einzelhandel und Verkaufsstände (Food) Bars und Diskotheken Imbisskonzepte und mobile Küche Food-Trucks Sonstige Großküchenplanung und Großküchentechnik Weitere, konkrete Referenzen aus unserem Leistungsspektrum nennen wir gerne auf Nachfrage. Noch besser aber ist: Sie vereinbaren gleich ein kostenloses Erstgespräch mit uns. Wir kommen gerne zu Ihnen und eruieren Ihre Wünsche und Vorhaben. Als erfahrenes und hochmotiviertes Planungsbüro, als Top-Dienstleister für die Großkücheneinrichtung und vor allem als echte Fans gelungener gastronomischer Einrichtungen und treuer Partner auf Augenhöhe. Gerne erhalten Sie auch vorab eine Broschüre über unser Leistungsspektrum und unsere Beratungs-Konzepte inkl. Firmenportrait unserer GmbH. Service Wenn's mal eilig wird: Ersatzteil-Service und Servicenetzwerk Kennen Sie das? Ihr Restaurant läuft auf Hochbetrieb, und plötzlich fällt der Pizzaofen oder Filter für den Eiswürfelbereiter aus, oder die Gummidichtung Ihrer Spülmaschine funktioniert nicht mehr richtig? Die Kaffeemühlen geben nur noch komische Geräusche von sich, der Kombidämpfer läuft aus und die Saladetten sind plötzlich handwarm? Alltagskatastrophe in der Gastronomie - jetzt braucht es einen kühlen Kopf und einen schnellen Ersatzteilservice für Großküchentechnik und Gastronomiebedarf! Hilfe naht: der Rund-Um Service und Ersatzteilfinder von Gastrozentrale Unter der Telefonnummer 0800-672 672 672 und hier im Webshop steht Ihnen unser Ersatzteile-Team zur Verfügung. Wir führen über 120.000 Ersatzteile für die Großküche, Gastronomie und Hotellerie und haben gute Chancen, dass auch Ihr gesuchtes Produkt darunter ist. Egal ob Brennerdeckel oder Drehknopf für den Gasgrill, ein Heizkörper für die gebrauchten Pizzaöfen, ein Thermostat für defekte Hähnchengrills, ein neuer Ventilator für den Konvektomaten, ein spezielles Scharnier für den Getränkekühlschrank oder einfach nur ein passender Friteusenkorb - wir finden mit Ihnen heraus, wo der Schuh drückt und handeln schnell und engagiert. Und wenn mal etwas außerhalb der Öffnungszeiten schief läuft, finden Sie mit unserem Ersatzteilfinder für Kochtechnik, Spültechnik, Kühltechnik und Lüftungstechnik rasch das passende Teil, das sofort automatisch für Sie bestellt wird. Mit unserem Riesen-Sortiment decken wir dabei folgende Marken und Gerätetypen für den Einsatz in Großküchen ab, z.B. Ersatzteile für Kochtechnik-Ersatzteile, z.B. Ventile und einen Einlaufhahn für Dampfgarer und Heißluftofen von Rational, Eloma, MKN, Convotherm und Unox Spültechnik-Ersatzteile, z.B. eine Dichtung oder ein Thermostat für eine (Hauben-)spülmaschine von Winterhalter, Meiko, Hobart, Stalgast und Colged Gas-Thermik-Teile für einen Gasofen und Gasgrill von Krefft, Baron, Ascoblock, Bertos und Heidebrenner Kältetechnik-Teile für einen Gewerbekühlschrank oder Schockfroster von Norcap, Irinox, ECO, COMPACT, Liebherr, KBS und GGG Frosttechnik-Artikel für Eisbereiter und Eiswürfelmaschinen von Hoshizaki, Wessamat, Manitowoc und Brema Ersatzartikel für einen Kühltisch, eine Kühltheke oder Getränketheke von KBS, Cool Compact, Chromornom, Cool Line, und Chromofair Austausch-Produkte für Arbeitschränke, Arbeitstische, Spültische und Edelstahlmöbel von GGG, Morgan, AfG, Lauterjung und GGM Reparatur-Teile für Salamander, Vakuumiergeräte, Aufschnittmaschinen und andere Gastrogeräte von Bartscher, Carpigiani, ADE, GRAEF Zubehör für Kaffeemühlen, Kaffeevollautomaten und Siebträgermaschinen von Jura, Saeco, Nespresso, Melitta, San Remo, Animo, Cimbali, La Marzocco, ECM, Gaggia und La Pavoni sowie Ersatzteile und Zubehör für den alltäglichen Gastronomiebedarf und Hotelbedarf wie Gemüseschneider (z.B. Robo Coupe, GAM) Müslispender (z.B: Frilich, Pulsiva), Entsafter (z.B. Santos, Gastroback), Mixer (z.B. Dynamics, Hamilton Beach) und nahezu alle anderen elektrischen und mechanischen Kleingeräte aus der Gastro. Mit unserem speziellen Ersatzteilfinder können Sie schnell nach Marke, Gerät und Seriennummer suchen - und sollten Sie einmal etwas nicht finden, versuchen wir gerne, weltweit das richtige Produkt zu beschaffen, wenn möglich auch mit 24 Stunden-Service oder Overnight-Lieferung. Tipps für langlebige Geräte - Installation nur durch den Fachmann - das Gastrozentrale Service-Netzwerk Apropos kaputte Geräte: Immer wieder erleben wir, dass technische Produkte deutlich länger halten könnten, wenn sie fachgerecht von einem zertifizierten Handwerker angeschlossen geworden wären. Egal ob Wasserfilter für Eiswürfelmaschinen oder Wasseranschluss für einen Dampfgarer - wer beim Anschluss spart, zahlt hinterher oft zweimal! Bei der Suche nach dem perfekten Anschluss-Service ist guter Rat jedoch oft teuer: Welcher lokale Installateur oder Elektriker ist auch für Großküchen-Produkte geeignet und bringt die richtige Erfahrung mit? Hier kommen wir ins Spiel: Mit unserem Service-Netzwerk für Anschluss, Reparatur und Wartung finden wir für Sie den richtigen Partner. So arbeiten wir bundesweit mit über 1.200 Elektrikern, Kältetechnikern, Lüftungsplanern und Installateuren zusammen. Denn Ihr Gerät soll ja nicht nur angeschlossen, sondern auch regelmäßig geprüft, gewartet und repariert werden. Damit Sie hier nur echte Gastro-Experten in Ihre Küche lassen, arbeiten wir nur mit Partnern zusammen, die für Ihr neues Gerät auch autorisiert sind. Und sollte tatsächlich einmal etwas sein, rufen Sie uns gerne an oder schreiben Sie uns eine Mail. Wir kümmern uns gern! 123 456 789 Kontaktieren Sie uns! name: Door2door
about:
There are gaps in every public transport network: At the outskirts of cities and in rural areas, in the evenings and on weekends. We identify these gaps, expand the network with a modern on-demand bus concept and integrate all existing offers into a smartphone app for citizens. This is the fastest way to wider public transport coverage. And the citizens are enthusiastic.

No bus station, a sparse timetable, special locations – every municipality has gaps in the network. Until now, citizens have used their cars to fill them. Our alternative: A public transport service with all the comfort of the car, in which the passenger can choose the pick-up and drop-off points. We combine all existing offers into the next public transport system. Efficient. Flexible. Digital.

www.facebook.com/door2doorHQ
twitter.com/door2door
www.instagram.com/door2door_team

name: Wildcorn
about:
Wildcorn erfindet das Snacken neu. 

In der Herstellung verzichten wir komplett auf Dinge, die entweder keiner kennt und keiner haben will: Angefangen damit, dass wir unseren Produkten keinen Zucker zusetzen und sie weder Konservierungsstoffe, noch künstliche Aromen oder Farbstoffe enthalten. Ach ja, bio und vegan sind wir auch.

name: refurbed
about: Refurbed is the fastest growing online marketplace for refurbished products in the german-speaking world. The startup, which is based in Vienna, sells renewed phones, laptops and tablets which are up to 40% cheaper and 100% more environmentally friendly than their brand-new, store-bought counterparts. Refurbed devices are renewed through a 40-step process, making them look like new and function like new. On top of that, each device comes with at least a 12 month guarantee.

name: School OS
about: School OS is one of the leading companies for E-school solutions. Its product School OS is the powerful AI-based education platform, which uses AI to analyze schools’ data to provide personal counseling to teachers and parents. School OS visualizes schools’ data to make education easy and more productive.  Today everything is switching to the digital format. Our solution offers electronic diary functionality to schools. School OS was created with the sole aim to make teaching and parenting more engaging, efficient and fun. It makes the communication between school and home easier, quicker and paper free. The whole learning process becomes easier not only for teachers, parents and students, businesses can also achieve better outcomes.  As for our partnership program, we are looking for local companies with connections in education that want to represent our solution locally. What our future business partners get:  - 0 capex - Ad network for extra revenue streams - Revenue share business model - Training for managers and admins  With the introduction of School OS we are making a big step towards 21st century e-learning environment.

name: United Signals
about:
Die United Signals GmbH mit Hauptsitz in Frankfurt am Main ist ein deutscher Spezialist für papierlose und einfach zu bedienende Kundenlösungen. Mit Produkten wie digitalem Onboarding, elektronischen Verträgen, Middle- und Backoffice-Systemen sowie Kundenportalen unterstützt sie Unternehmen aller Branchen.

Durch die White-Label-Fähigkeit und die Flexibilität unserer Lösung lassen sich mit der Software in kurzer Zeit beliebige Formulare oder Verträge in eine digitale Version umwandeln, die kontaktlos, auch von zu Hause oder mobil, unterschrieben werden können. Sie ist mehrsprachig und kann problemlos in bestehende Systemlandschaften integriert werden.

name: Fanmiles
about: Launched in September 2015, Fanmiles is on a mission to provide a valuable, seamless & trustworthy loyalty experience for customers and businesses alike. With an open loyalty platform to create and manage loyalty campaigns, Fanmiles gives forward-thinking businesses the tools and technology they need to run data-driven, white label loyalty programs that increase retention and generate revenue.

name: Bragi
about:
Bragi was founded in 2013 and launched the world's first Truly Wireless Earphones in 2015. Since then Bragi has evolved from a promising startup to a market-moving creator of innovative technology, opening the new category of Truly Wireless Earphones. 

Bragi transformed into a software enabler for consumer brands, focusing on scaling its technology after investing more than $90 million in software and AI.

Bragi's Software Platform consists of an earphone OS and a smartphone App embedding advanced AI and efficient software. For more information about Bragi's Software Platform, visit www.bragi.com.

name: Aerobo
about: Aerobo specializes in high-quality, professional aerial filming and drone cinematography. We are an FAA Part 107 Compliant Drone Service provider.  Aerobo operates drones for clients across multiple verticals with a particular focus in media.  Our teams of drone pilots are fully licensed, certified, and insured for both daylight and nighttime shoots.  Aerobo serves clients nationwide with hubs in New York, Los Angeles, Atlanta, New Orleans, Chicago, Miami,  Albuquerque and Montreal.

name: Scoutbee
about:
scoutbee’s market-leading supplier data platform empowers procurement professionals to enhance their master data, make better sourcing decisions, and find and onboard new suppliers across the world. Powered by AI and ML, scoutbee enables faster end-to-end strategic sourcing projects with up to 90% less effort versus traditional methods. By providing comprehensive and dynamic supplier data, scoutbee facilitates proactive sourcing decisions that strengthen supply chain resilience, improve sustainability, drive innovation, time to market and diversity. scoutbee is trusted by industry leaders in automotive, agriculture, energy, FMCG, industrial machinery and the Life Science sector. Having won many prestigious awards including Gartner’s Cool Vendor and Spend Matter 50 Vendors to Watch, scoutbee is a recognized leader in AI-driven procurement technology.

scoutbee’s customers include companies such as Unilever, Audi, Siemens, and many more.

name: Compado
about:
Compado is the market leader in developing automated ranking and recommendation technology for commercial products. Grounded in big data, our technology lists, ranks and automatically recommends commercial products based on our machine learning software. 

Operating in more than 70 countries, we empower high-profile consumer brands such as Hello Fresh, Babbel, Parship and others to achieve outstanding growth by delivering interested clients to our partners and helping them scale their online performance.

name: Virtual Content Group
about:
Virtual Content Group (VCG) is a leading global VR content company offering end-to-end production, post-production and distribution services. With a background in stereoscopic 3D, operations spanning thirteen countries and over 50 clients worldwide, VCG is an international powerhouse with a focus on high-end brand campaigns and award-winning factual content. The company has delivered more than a hundred 360 degree videos and Virtual Reality projects and owns distribution rights to a growing library of over eighty 3rd-party productions. 

VCG is a merged entity of three businesses from France, Germany and Australia. The three respective CEOs have decided to merge their businesses and re-brand as Virtual Content Group to scale faster, as well as to attract larger clients and investors. about: Rna Diagnostics Inc. is an early-stage molecular diagnostics company developing medical diagnostic tools to assist in the management of cancer. RDA can determine whether chemotherapy is working effectively in the individual patient early in treatment thereby guiding clinical decision making.

name: Caresyntax
about: Caresyntax is on a mission to make surgery smarter and safer. Our enterprise-grade digital surgery platform delivers actionable insights to improve patient outcomes by using proprietary software and AI to analyze large volumes of video, audio, images, device data, clinical, and operational data in and around the OR. This real world evidence can be used by the care team live, during a procedure and accessed by those outside the operating room via the platform’s dedicated telehealth link. After a procedure, the Caresyntax platform provides insights that help: surgeons benchmark and improve their care, hospital administrators use surgical resources more efficiently, medical device companies advance better products, and insurance companies understand risk and devise more tailored policies. Headquartered in Boston, Caresyntax software is used in more than 4,000 operating rooms worldwide and supports surgical teams in over two million procedures per year.

about: Caresyntax is on a mission to make surgery smarter and safer. name: CleverShuttle
about:
CleverShuttle is Germany's leading operator for on-demand ride-pooling services.

We partner with cities and public transport authorities to put on-demand transport on the road efficiently, so that more people can have convenient and affordable access to sustainable mobility. We want to see on-demand ride-pooling become fully integrated into our public transport systems – because only then will it be a real alternative to personal car ownership. 

With over six years of experience in demand-responsive transport (DRT), we cover all operational aspects of on-demand ride-pooling – ranging from demand forecasting and shift planning, through intelligent traffic control, to driver- and charge-management for electric fleets.

Our on-demand ride-pooling services provide people with a flexible mode of door-to-door transportation, where riders share a vehicle with others who are going in the same direction. Our fleets are electric and run on renewable energy. This lowers costs for riders while also decreasing traffic congestion and harmful emissions.

We currently operate on-demand services in seven German cities. Since starting out in 2014, we’ve helped over five million people get where they need to go.

Join us for the ride and help us shape the future of mobility: We are always looking for smart, dedicated, and open-minded people to join the team!
_______________________________________________________

CleverShuttle is a subsidiary of Deutsche Bahn AG who acquired a majority stake in the company in 2018. In 2019, Japan-based Mitsui & Co., Ltd. joined as a strategic investor, acquiring 10% of the company.

» www.clevershuttle.de

name: Evana
about:
EVANA is a technology company that specialises in analysing databases and documents using AI algorithms. Our current markets are the real estate, legal, banking and insurance sectors which face challenges due to the volumes of data they have to handle and the need to process this quickly with a high level of accuracy. 

EVANA’s Head Office is located in Frankfurt within short distance to many relevant real estate, legal and banking clients. Saarbrücken is the location where all R&D activities of EVANA are concentrated as it is considered to be one of the strongest locations for the IT industry in Germany. The city has gained this reputation not just from the University of the Saarland - the Max Planck Institute, the German Research Center for Artificial Intelligence as well as numerous other specialist IT businesses all characterise the state capital of the Saarland. A further branch office is located in Berlin.

The name EVANA is made up of the terms Evaluation & Analytics.

EVANA offers AI powered data room and document management. 

The EVANA360 platform can be used both for life cycle document and data management as well as for transaction and due diligence processes.

Alongside algorithmic evaluations and analytics the team is supported by legal specialists who verify the results obtained and ensure they are legally sound. 

As part of our product range, we offer semi-automated solutions to support our clients in GDPR compliance.

name: Kippie
about: Kippie is a conversational UI handling all the signup process including (but not limited to) quotation, extra details, payment and on-boarding - where we provide you with the tools to up-sell, cross sell and increase retention rates and profits as well as rich analytics to understand your customer journeys and their behaviours - for insurers. What this all means specifically - in features that we can provide for you: - Journey fall-through automatically reduced a 30%* (from get a quote to payment completed). - 13%* Upsells on a regular form. - One of the most advanced Fraud prevention detectors in the market (this is a separate product). - ...

name: Celularity
about: Celularity, headquartered in Florham Park, N.J., is a clinical stage biotechnology company leading the next evolution in cellular medicine by delivering off-the-shelf allogeneic placenta-derived cellular therapies at unparalleled scale, quality and economics. Celularity’s innovative approach to cell therapy harnesses the unique therapeutic potential locked within the postpartum placenta. Through nature’s immunotherapy engine – the placenta – Celularity is leading the next evolution of cellular medicine with placenta-derived T cells, NK cells, and pluripotent stem cells to target unmet and underserved clinical needs in cancer, infectious and degenerative diseases. To learn more visit celularity.com.

name: Planetary Resources
about: The asteroid mining company.  Founded in 2009 by Eric Anderson and Peter H. Diamandis, M.D., Planetary Resources, Inc. is establishing a new paradigm for resource utilization that will bring the solar system within humanity’s economic sphere of influence by enabling low-cost robotic exploration and commercial development of asteroids.  Asteroid mining will open a trillion-dollar industry and provide a near-infinite supply of precious resources to support humanity’s growth both on this planet and off. Please visit www.planetaryresources.com to learn more about the company’s mission, product offerings and world-class team.

name: vAtomic Systems
about: In a world where bits are easily copied, and ownership and authenticity are in constant flux, we have become accustomed to value bits differently than tangible goods. vAtomic Systems Inc. (VSI) dissolves the boundaries between bits and atoms, enabling a new digital asset class. Smart objects called virtual atoms--or “vAtoms”--leverage exponential advances in cloud computing, mobile devices and consensus ledger technology (blockchains) to provide a level of end-user experience, authenticity and trust never before possible.

name: Zazu
about: Zazu is a money app that helps you store, use and learn about money. It’s free to join, easy to understand and makes managing money effortless.

name: Itcher
about:
itcher solves the world’s entertainment discovery problem through a well-tested artificial intelligence (“AI”) technology that connects people (not products!) through entertainment. We help individuals solve the recurring problem around what to do in their spare time: 

- Which movie to watch?
- Which artist/song to listen to?
- Which book to read?
- Which game to play?

itcher is a mobile and voice app that generates book, movie, TV series, music and game recommendations personalised to each user's taste.

People’s free time is valuable and current recommendation products are not great.   But itcher discovers ‘hidden gems’ differently to any other product out there. We link like-minded people, segmenting them by their reviews across four entertainment verticals and enabling them to communicate and discover through one another. 

We have been quoted in media to be “The Trip Advisor for Entertainment.” We were also chosen by Google Home as launch partner within their entertainment “skills”.  This is consistent with our grand vision.  We aim to power recommendations across all categories in the future.

We will soon (August 2018) be deploying "Couple Recommendations" in an effort to reduce friction between spouses on Friday and Saturday evenings. itcher users will be able to link their profiles to one another to get movie and tv show recommendations that they'll both enjoy. We see this as a game changer, and unique to the industry.
 
Initially a pure B2C business, we have expanded into B2B serving now as a back-end engine powering discovery of streaming content within/across delivery platforms.

itcher also has an online magazine ( itcher.com/mag ), covering curated entertainment recommendations for movies, TV shows books, music and games.

We are a friendly and fun, experienced international team who come from a variety of backgrounds but who share a passion for technology and entertainment.

In doing so, we are reshaping the way luxury watches are bought and sold today.

With our offices in Cologne, Zug, London, Hong Kong, and more, we have established CHRONEXT worldwide and continue to grow. about:

This syndication economy system can be applied to a multitude of industries, including insurance, venture capital, and many more. Jointer’s first use case will be commercial real estate.

It runs on the robust API engine, which fully automatically consolidates and unifies data from various custodian banks, making portfolio and client information accessible anywhere, anytime and from any device with Internet access.

Our smart solution for digital transformation allows wealth managers to focus on growing their business and staying competitive in a rapidly changing world. 

WealthArc was founded on the belief that Wealth Management and Private Banking can and should benefit from the latest technologies and digital innovations, in line with other industries, to accelerate growth and attract new generations of clients. 

The company collaborates closely with Microsoft, Swisscom or Refinitiv and has been recognized in many acceleration programs: F10 Incubator, Fidelity Investments Accelerator and Google for Startups Residency Program among others. We have also held a title on the winning list of WealthBriefing European Awards 2017 – in two categories.

Since receiving funding in 2015, we’ve developed a unique portfolio management platform that works with 35+ custodian banks and third-party data providers like Refinitiv and Investment Navigator. Our easy to use software takes only 48 hours to set up. We are currently offering customers a 3-month pilot.

Connect with us to keep up to date with WealthArc news and follow the latest industry trends which matter to your business.

about:

We are reinventing the way flowers and plants are enjoyed, from our farmers to our customers' doors. Because we believe small gestures and details can change everything and we want to help people bring these small gestures into their day-to-day and help them be with their loved ones when they can't.

Colvin currently operates in 4 countries and has offices in Barcelona, but with a remote-first culture. Work from anywhere when you feel like or come and meet the team at the office. We recently closed our €45M financing and we’ve been recognized as LinkedIn's Top 2 Startup 2020 in Spain. But all of that is just the beginning of a long journey to continue inspiring people to connect more often and disrupt the floriculture and gifting space globally.

name: Tripaneer
about: Tripaneer is the world’s leading marketplace to discover, plan and safely book unique travel experiences. We are specialized in holidays that include yoga, surf, safaris, motorcycling, horse riding, martial arts, and many more. We’re passionate about building a platform that our customers and partners love to use.  We love to travel and we want to share our excitement with you. That’s why we want to enrich your life with unforgettable travel experiences.   We are a fast growing startup that was founded in 2013. We have 200+ Tripaneers working from our office in Amsterdam and around the world. We are driven to serve our customers and to best understand what makes a travel experience unforgettable and how we can help as many people as people to enjoy a life-enriching experience. We’re an inquisitive team of creative problem solvers, tech wizards, and passionate travelers. We’re proud to be leading the charge in bringing the experience in the travel industry online.  Our work is our life's passion. Together, we work hard and we laugh a lot. The Tripaneer team culture encourages learning, innovation, and transparency. We are dedicated to providing user-centric services, not only for our customers but also for our partners and the small-to-medium-sized holiday organizers we work closely with.  Be it between colleagues, with our customers, partners, or organizers, we treat each one of our relationships with utmost care and continuously seek to add value and enhance their lives and/or business however we can.   As part of the long-term key drivers of our culture and business, Tripaneers share the following three core values: * Stronger together | Be empathetic * Own it! | Take responsibility * Awesome always | Be the best you can be  As we’re growing rapidly, we’re constantly looking to improve our team with talented people. Are you ready for your next step in your career?

name: PlanRadar
about:
PlanRadar is a cloudbased SaaS (Software as a Service) platform for construction documentation and defect management in real estate projects. In each real estate project are in average 1-2 defects per 10m² - we help to manage them!
 
Our solution with web access and native apps for smartphones and tablets supports the user in recording, documentation, communication and tracking of tasks and defects. Project managers, architects, technicians and facility & property managers can record tasks, defects, quality checks, etc. in a cost & time saving way directly on the construction site with their tablet or smartphone and assign them in real time to the responsible project stakeholders.

The problems of construction documentation and defect management leading to unsatisfying adjustment of defects and additional costs are:
- the annoying and inefficient recording of tasks and defects
- the inefficient communication with other project stakeholders
- the problems according to incomplete communication, inconsistent versioning and information opacity

PlanRadar is the digital solution of this process and is realizing cost and time savings of 60-70%. 

PlanRadar is cloudbased, that means there is no installation required and it can be used anywhere and anytime, also offline. PlanRadar can be used on all browsers and platforms with native apps for smartphones and tablets. 

The user uploads blueprints and is able to pin any defects or tasks directly via his smartphone or tablet on the blueprint and then share and communicate them with other project stakeholders (e.g. suppliers, owners, etc.) and also track and follow up the enhancements. The whole communication and workflow is documented and can be used for reports and revision.

Your advantages are: 
- Cloudbased (no installation; used anywhere, anytime, also offline)
- Ease of Use (fast, intuitive; no training (support effort/user/year ca. 1h)
- All platforms (browsers, tablets, smartphones).

name: Beekin

Backed by a team of urban economists, AI PhDs and ex-CRE investors, Beekin marries data science with a deep understanding of real estate. At Beekin, we don't compete, we collaborate. 

We are named after the Bee - which survived 60 million years of evolution, through relentless collaboration.Data will build that kinship in real estate. 

Let's collaborate, let's Beekin

about: Quid is a new way to help employees of privately-held companies get the liquidity they need to pay for life today â€“  without selling the stock options theyâ€™ve earned for a fraction of what theyâ€™ll someday be worth.   Whether you need money to buy a home, start a family, diversify your portfolio or invest in a new opportunity, Quid can provide you with cash faster than selling your shares â€“ and you donâ€™t have to give up your shares.

name: DynaPass
about:
DynaPass Inc. is the leading provider of out of band two-factor authentication solutions to companies worldwide. Founded in 2011, with locations in the United States and Sweden, led by industry experts providing best in class security solutions to key verticals such as Healthcare, Education, Financial Services, and Subscription Based Services. 

The flagship patented security solution, DynaPass (U.S. Patent no. 6,993,658),  offers strong authentication for enterprise and consumer applications. The DynaPass Security Platform allows users to simply receive an OTP (One Time Password) via SMS text message to authenticate when accessing network assets. By leveraging a device every user already has, a mobile phone, the patented DynaPass Security Solution enables rapid deployment of a zero footprint technology and cost-effective two-factor authentication.

DynaPass, Inc. has been driven by the belief that security and simplicity are intrinsically tied. The mobile phone is the ideal tool to accomplish both. It provides the strong, out-of-band security that is critical to protecting against today’s threats as well as the simplicity afforded by the use of a ubiquitous device.

DynaPass was awarded the  Red Herring Top 100 Global Technologies and was awarded the “Oscars of Wireless”, WBI Award for Wireless Broadband Innovation.

name: Rent2Buy
about:
Rent2Buy is the global eMarketplace to rent or lease anything with the option to buy it. Rent2Buy works for consumers who are looking to try out a big ticket item before making a commitment, or for those short on cash but will have the money later.

The Rent2Buy system puts consumers on the path to big ticket purchases without having to apply for a loan. Instead, the rental fee is applied as a down payment toward their future purchase of the item, or they can walk away. Conversely, sellers are exposed to a larger base of potential buyers who are motivated to buy.

Rent2Buy is the brainchild of developer Moti Kahana, who pioneered the direct-to-consumer sale of used cars at discounted prices through his Automoti system. In 2009 Kahana sold Automoti to Hertz Rent-A-Car, which became Hertz Rent2Buy.

name: tapcore
about:
Tapcore serves over 150 million ad requests daily, and is the only technology on the market that allows mobile developers to detect illegal copies of their mobile applications and generate revenue from them.

When your app is pirated, the Tapcore SDK starts displaying high-quality targeted ads to the pirated user. It does not compete with with existing in-app monetization strategies and plays well with any ad network.

We can't stop piracy, but we can help you get well-deserved compensation for pirated installations of your IP!

name: Velocity
about: Velocity provides revenue based financing, up to Rs 3 crores, for marketing and inventory spends of online businesses. Our vision is to be the easiest and fastest way for new age businesses to raise growth capital. Being founders ourselves, we strongly felt the need of a fast, flexible and non-dilutive mode of financing. Unhappy with the existing options, we decided to build it ourselves!

name: Nobul
about:
Nobul is the world’s first and only technology-driven real estate marketplace where every agent, from every brokerage, can compete for the consumer’s business.  We deliver consumer choice, agent accountability and overall real estate transparency.                                             
This is how our name, Nobul, came about.  Our Founder and CEO Regan McGee came up with the word himself and it alludes to two things. First, the fact that we have the "noble" goal of demystifying and bringing transparency to the real estate market. Second, is the fact that on our platform, we don't allow room for any "B.S." at any time. We empower customers by giving them access to all the information they need to learn about our agents, including sales history, verified reviews, and more. This is something we are all very proud of!

name: Templarbit
about: Developer-oriented security platform, helping small and large companies protect their software from malicious activity

name: Contentflow
about: Contentflow is the global Next-Gen SaaS solution for multichannel, independent live streaming for events, conferences and media coverage.  Sebastian Serafin (CEO of Contentflow) started as an Event Manager in Berlin. Part of his role included hosting several international conferences, and he wanted to live stream these events across all of their channels to increase awareness and audience engagement. However, he also wanted these recordings to be available as soon as possible for marketing purposes in addition to documentation. He quickly found out two things about video live streaming: it would not be easy, and it would not be cheap. Actually, after shopping around for a provider who could provide this service, he realized that what he was asking for would be very complicated, and in turn, very expensive.   Sebastian and Gregor Landwehr (COO of Contentflow) knew then that they might have something. And that led to the birth of Contentflow. Four years later, Contentflow continues to succeed and soar. For example, Online Marketing Rockstars (OMR), the largest online marketing conference worldwide (40,000+ attendees) uses Contentflow to live broadcast on social media, including 102 different and simultaneous stream channels, including Facebook, YouTube, websites, etc.    Some exclusive features of Contentflow include: an Embeddable Video Player (allows rewinding of live stream in real time), Multistream (enables distribution of live stream among multiple platforms simultaneously), Audience Analytics (collects viewer data including number of streams and provides geolocation map), Overlay Graphic (adds branding and static overlay graphic during livestream) and Cloud-Based editing (allows immediate editing, cutting and sharing while streaming). With these premier features, Contentflow users from a variety of industries can easily utilize this all-in-one live streaming platform to distribute live content to increase reach, engagement and revenue.

name: HousingAnywhere
about:
Helping people find housing, anywhere. With this vision, HousingAnywhere has been transforming the rental market since its founding in 2009 by developing the most technologically advanced platform in the rental market. HousingAnywhere opens the doors to a home across Europe for students, expats and young professionals to securely rent rooms or apartments from landlords and property managers on the HousingAnywhere platform. 

Over the last years, the platform has become a place where more than 10 million users search for rooms and apartments. At HousingAnywhere, we believe that we can improve the rental experience for all tenants and landlords with our modern and user-friendly rental platform. 

We are a team of over 120 people based in Rotterdam with a passion for helping people. At HousingAnywhere we bring together people from more than 40 different nationalities and backgrounds. We are committed to a diverse and inclusive culture and believe that it is an important contributor to our business success.

We are proud that HousingAnywhere has been awarded ‘Most Innovative Company’ and listed one of Deloitte’s Fast50 Growing Companies in the Netherlands as well as made it to the DeloitsFast500 in Europe. 

Join our team, check out our career opportunities at https://careers.housinganywhere.com/

name: Ravean
about:
Let’s be real here for a moment, we’re not the first people to come up with the idea of heated jackets. We’re just the first ones to do it right. 

By doing it right we mean our jackets look good, they’re durable, they’re affordable and they integrate our technology seamlessly and unobtrusively. Finally there’s a heated jacket you can wear with equal comfort and style from the mountains to the office without missing a beat. Sure it’s been tried before but other solutions have been pricey, ugly and the technology was problematic. Ravean has addressed and solved each of these issues to present jackets you can wear anywhere, that are as stylish and durable as they are warm and cozy.

We are an end-to-end solution to capture, transform, and stream real human holograms that can be experienced through any device, browser, or VR/AR headset. 

In short, we help put real people (not avatars) inside of immersive 3D experiences, leading to more authentic human connection in digital worlds and the metaverse. 

Our solution includes enterprise-grade hologram Capture stages available in a wide variety of camera arrays, a cutting-edge software stack to Transform (fuse, edit, and compress) holograms using proprietary computer vision and machine learning models, and a publishing suite to integrate your photoreal holograms into digital experiences that can be viewed from any angle across any device. This empowers new dimensions of experiencing content, and has profound applications across communications, entertainment, commerce, and education.

8i's customers include innovative organizations across technology, media, retail, manufacturing, and government (Softbank, US Army, Google, Verizon, Walmart) and we are backed by leading investors including VCs and media giants (One Ventures, Verizon, RRE, LG Tech Ventures, Founder's Fund, Hearst). Founded in May 2014, 8i is based in Los Angeles with offices in Chicago and Wellington, New Zealand. Get in touch to see how holograms can be a game-changer for your organization. Learn more at https://8i.com.

about:
Clover Health (NASDAQ: CLOV) is a data-focused health insurance company driving to improve the overall state of healthcare in America. Clover focuses on disrupting the Medicare Advantage space by integrating innovation and technology into its processes. By harnessing the power of analytics and its proprietary technology, it gathers and analyzes health and behavioral data to optimize medical outcomes and reduce avoidable costs for patients.

Unlike other health insurance companies also embracing preventive health, Clover’s Medicare Advantage plans are built on technology from the ground-up. Integrating our systems with doctors, clinicians, and nurse practitioners, Clover Health’s data team helps healthcare professionals in the field intervene directly into patients’ wellness to help them avoid acute health episodes. Clover boasts a risk-scoring system that monitors the patients’ conditions in real-time and therefore assists healthcare practitioners in formulating personalized care plans. This strategy is doubly effective as not only does it allow for the prompt creation of treatment plans, but it also prevents the deterioration of patients’ conditions and averts the occurrence of acute health episodes. 

Since its official launch in 2014, Clover Health has witnessed substantial growth as it currently serves more than 66,300 members across eight states. The company has offices in Nashville, San Francisco, Jersey City, and Hong Kong.

We are hiring software engineers, data scientists, designers and product folks who can help us understand our members’ wellness and steer them clear of any health risks down the road.

If you’re a passionate person and interested in changing healthcare for the better, then Clover Health may just be the place for you.

While this type of speculative investment has so far only been accessible to investors who have a minimum investment of EUR 500,000 or more, Radenbrock offers a comparable and above-average performance from an investment of EUR 25,000.

Although there are already some Robo Advisor on the market, almost all their trading strategies are based on ETFs, a passive investment and the occasional rebalancing of the portfolio. The yields of this passive asset management are heavily dependent on the development of the overall market. Radenbrock's strategies, on the other hand, make use of market inefficiency in comparatively short periods of time and are thus independent of the overall market or possible shortcomings.

name: InfanDx
about:
InfanDx AG is a privately held company incorporated in 2010 in Cologne, Germany, focusing on the development and commercialization of diagnostic solutions for newborns. 
The Company’s proprietary lead product in clinical development is the InfanDx HypoxE-test® designed for the reliable identification of hypoxic-ischemic encephalopathy (HIE) within the first hours of birth. HIE as a consequence of perinatal asphyxia (oxygen deficit during birth) can result in life-long disabilities. The long-term detrimental effects of HIE can be mitigated and even prevented by neuroprotective hypothermia treatment. However, this burdensome therapy has to be initiated within six hours of birth to be effective, requiring suitable diagnostic methods to reliably and timely identify the affected newborns. 
While standard-of-care diagnostic methods cannot deliver a conclusive diagnosis of HIE within this time frame, the rapid InfanDx HypoxE-test® is designed to support clinicians in the timely decision whether newborns require neuroprotective hypothermia treatment.

name: Outbank
about:
Was macht Outbank aus? Wir sind ein Team. Mit Experten aus aller Welt. Mit Ideen und dem Wunsch, gemeinsam ein neues Banking-Erlebnis zu erschaffen. Als Outbank verbinden wir Menschen mit tausenden von Banken, unterstützen sie im täglichen Vermögensmanagement und ermöglichen ihnen komplette Finanzfreiheit. Als Team arbeiten wir täglich an einer App, die uns stolz macht. Seit über 15 Jahren setzen wir uns mit Hingabe dafür ein, die Bankgeschäfte unserer User mobiler, einfacher und sicherer zu machen. Wir wollen helfen, die eigenen Finanzen besser zu verstehen.

Outbank ist eine der führenden Apps für persönliches Finanzmanagement im deutschen Markt. Seit 2005 unterstützt die App ihre Nutzer dabei, Klarheit über die eigene Finanzlage zu erhalten. Nutzer sollen durch Outbank Sparpotentiale bei ihren Ausgaben identifizieren und Alternativen zu teuren Verträgen und Abos erhalten. Kern der App liegt in der übersichtlichen Darstellung von Finanzdaten eines Nutzers aus über 4.000 angebundenen Finanzinstituten.

Sicheres mobiles Banking, Übersicht über Fixkosten, Budgetplanung, Vertragskündigung und -wechsel sowie Finanzanalyse – all das bietet Outbank für iOS, macOS und Android.
