about: Accessible Media Inc. (AMI) is a not-for-profit multimedia organization serving more than five million Canadians who are blind, partially sighted, deaf, hard of hearing, mobility or print restricted. Operating three broadcast services, AMI-tv and AMI-audio in English and AMI-télé in French, AMI’s mission is to make accessible media for all Canadians. To learn more visit AMI.ca and AMItele.ca.

name: Quiqup
about:
Quiqup is changing the way goods move around the city. 

We’re creating the next generation of delivery solutions to suit shoppers’ ever-increasing demands.  We offer on demand, same day and scheduled deliveries businesses can control, a fleet of couriers anyone can tap into and a platform to help manage and automate deliveries.

We also work with large businesses to design custom logistics solutions, using our modular tech and operations to create services built with business needs in mind.

In short, we're reinventing the last-mile - for better business, better living and better cities.

name: R5FX
about:
R5 provides a new electronic marketplace for emerging market foreign exchange (EMFX) and electronic non-deliverable forwards (eNDF)

Regulation requires Foreign Exchange trading banks to drastically change their current trading channels for BRICS and other Emerging Market/NDF currency pairs. These currencies have been traded and fixed over a number of old, difficult to track and inefficient methods. The market has been opaque and liable to imperfect price movements to the detriment of both banks and their customers, hence the regulators desire for change. 

R5 has built an electronic marketplace that not only satisfies these new legal requirements, but also specialises in the fast growing transaction volumes in BRIC and emerging economy currencies.

R5's liquidity pool for eNDF's and EMFX focuses on leading the market change from voice to screen in BRICS and local currency trading. It provides a faster, more efficient alternative for anyone 'FX trading in the New World'.

name: Synergist
about:
Our mission is to radically improve society by supporting and empowering social movements. We believe that this new generation of social entrepreneurs has what it takes to tackle poverty, problems in education, civil rights issues, cancers, disconnectivity, environmental hazards, energy dependence, and more. 
 
Our role in all of this? We are providing people with the tools and community they need to make an impact. 
 
Join us on our journey to make the world a better place.

name: Riot Micro
about: Riot develops industry-leading wireless chipsets for smart objects in the Internet of Things. Our breakthrough IoT platform-on-a-chip simplifies cellular connectivity for current-generation applications such as smart metering and vehicle telematics, as well as a new generation of smart objects from wearables and smoke detectors to parking meters and traffic lights.

name: CrowdDesk
about:
Wir schaffen für jedes Unternehmen einen einfachen und digitalen Kapitalzugang.

Die Aufnahme und die Vermittlung von Kapital gehört für Unternehmen zu den komplexesten und reguliertesten Prozessen, die es überhaupt gibt. Dafür hat portagon eine Software gebaut, die alle Entscheidungsprozesse einfach, digital und rechtssicher darstellt. So digitalisieren wir durch unsere Produkte und Leistungen das Geschäft der Kapitalaufnahme und -vermittlung für Unternehmen, Banken, Emissionshäuser und Finanzvermittler. 

Das geschieht mit unserer White-Label-Lösung. Das bedeutet, dass unsere Kunden in den Vordergrund treten. Von portagon ist lediglich ein Investment-Button zu sehen, der sich unkompliziert auf die bestehende Unternehmenswebsite integrieren lässt. Dahinter stellen wir die technische Infrastruktur zur Verfügung, die jedem Unternehmen einen kosteneffizienten und vollständig automatisierten Kapitalzugang ermöglicht.  

Jedes Unternehmen erhält so einen eigenständigen Kapitalzugang über einen Investment-Button auf der eigenen Website, über eine separate Website oder mithilfe einer eigenen Plattform. Sie sind unabhängig von Dritten in ihren Investitionsentscheidungen und ihrer Kapitalbeschaffung. Wir stellen unseren Kunden einen Modulbaukasten zur Verfügung, der die technologische Infrastruktur umfasst und es ermöglicht, die rechtliche Strukturierung, die Vertriebsstrategie und einen professionellen Anlegerservice vollständig digital abzuwickeln. 

Für Banken, Emissionshäuser und Finanzvermittler treiben wir außerdem die Digitalisierung ihrer Geschäftsmodelle voran und eröffnen neue Finanzierungswege für deren Firmen- und Privatkunden. 

Über 500 Projekte bei einem Projektvolumen von mehr als 800 Millionen Euro hat portagon bereits begleitet. Rund 300 Kunden nutzen unsere Software-Lösung.

about: Our mission is to make healthcare more accessible and affordable. Tabeo offers payments and online patient experience tools for medical professionals. We work with 5,000+ specialists and are the #1 finance provider for private healthcare in the UK.

name: Xtensio
about:
Xtensio is a strategy and communications platform that allows teams to create, collaborate on, share and present with ease. Over 350,000 consultants, agencies, entrepreneurs and educators use Xtensio to build smarter documents and streamline their workflow.

Xtensio facilitates exchange of ideas to turn business goals into a reality. From entrepreneurs launching their company, to marketing teams promoting global brands and beyond, the tool helps users capture their vision with smart, beautiful documents, web pages and presentations. By combining the design capabilities of a website builder with the collaborative functionality of a content editor, we aim to revolutionize how businesses communicate in a world where perpetual innovation is the new normal.

Launched in 2015, Xtensio is the bootstrapping effort of Fake Crow (www.fakecrow.com), a creative product design studio that specializes in digital solutions for forward-thinking companies. Xtensio began as a creator for startups to visualize their company profile and show investors what they’re all about. So we began to turn our into a toolbox that not only offers presentation tools but also interactive templates that will be useful during research, brainstorming, planning and strategy phases of a company. Today, Xtensio fosters the exchange of ideas, transforming a vision into tangible pages of communication. Our small-but-mighty team of entrepreneurs, designers, and writers adheres to the lean mentality by generating real value for our users without wasting resources. Based in Los Angeles, California, Xtensio is defined by the creativity, cultural vibrancy and innovative spirit that permeates the city.

Sign up for FREE and learn more about how Xtensio can help you at www.xtensio.com, and follow us on Facebook, Twitter, and LinkedIn to keep up with product news and updates.

Based on proprietary, machine-learning-supported risk models, fully digitized processes and a highly scalable tech platform, Billie offers freedom to big and small businesses alike through fast liquidity, automated workflows and access to modern payment solutions. Billie was founded in 2016 by the former founders of Zencap (Exit to Funding Circle). Billie is based in Berlin and employs over 130 people from over 35 countries. name: AIR6 Systems
DexLeChem
about:
Services in Chemistry for a Sustainable World

Founded out of the Cluster of Excellence UniCat DexLeChem is a high-tech startup specialized in homogeneous catalysis. Looking from the perspective of Green Chemistry, the company provides innovative solutions for the chemical-pharmaceutical production leading to considerable competitive advantages. Our portfolio ranges from process optimization to the development of new routes of synthesis. 
By applying an agile project management tool (Scrum) development times are reduced by up to 30% compared to conventional development projects. This ensures fast, competent and customer-oriented solutions presented in ready-to-implement reports. Our interdisciplinary team currently counts twelve employees. The company’s headquarters is located at the CoLaborator in the heart of Berlin.

Areas of Expertise 
Combining various scientific disciplines distinguishes DexLeChem from pure organic chemists: technical chemistry, homogeneous (chiral) catalysis, process engineering and theoretical physics are deployed in each development project guaranteeing innovative solutions that are applicable in our customer’s production facilities. With a strong background in reaction engineering combined with computational chemistry we are experts in designing and optimizing production processes:
• Process optimization & scale-up
• Separation approaches (liquid-liquid separation)
• Simulations
• Synthesis design

Services 
Since the unique combination of our technical expertise is applicable in different phases of a product’s lifecycle our services support the optimization of already implemented as well as the development of new chemical production processes. Additionally, we offer a licensing opportunity for the metal-free and highly chemoselective reduction of nitro compounds to amines (WO 2014/037444 A1) as green alternative to traditional methods.

Learnship is the world’s leading provider of online, face-to-face language and intercultural training, with more than 1,000 language trainers working with 25,000 learners a year at more than 2,000 corporate clients. 
 
Learnship’s success is built on its ongoing strategy to combine human-centered learning design with transformational technology and progressive pedagogy to create the ultimate language learning experience for learners, trainers, and program managers.
 
The company's award-winning Virtual Classroom gives learners the personal coaching benefits of traditional on-site training with the convenience, flexibility, and cost-benefits of online learning. 
 
Every learner is matched with the trainer best-qualified to meet their individual needs, with personalized training programs available in 14 languages, alongside specialist courses in executive coaching, communication skills, relocation, and intercultural training. 
 
Learnship's highly-qualified trainers are also graduates of the Learnship Academy where they become fluent in the effective online, face-to-face learning methods that the company has refined over the past ten years, building on the experience of tens of thousands of client engagements.  
 
Learnship has also digitally transformed the entire learning management process for program managers in HR, including global deployment, learner assessment, onboarding, process automation, quality assurance, and real-time reporting.

name: Erydel
about: EryDel is a multi-asset, clinical stage biopharmaceutical company headquartered in Bresso (Milan), Italy dedicated to developing and commercializing novel treatments for rare diseases with high unmet need. In 2018 EryDel received the “Most Innovative StartUp Italia Award” chosen from startups across all industries. EryDel specializes in the delivery of drugs using the patient’s own red blood cells. The lead product candidate, EryDex, is currently in Phase III development for the treatment of Ataxia Telangiectasia (AT), a rare neurological disorder for which no established therapy is currently available. EryDex received Orphan Drug designation for the treatment of AT both from FDA and EMA

name: TransFICC
about:
TransFICC is an e-trading technology company, providing connectivity and workflow solutions for banks and asset managers operating in the Fixed Income and Derivatives markets. 

Its "One API for eTrading" product provides clients with an alternative to maintaining connectivity with multiple e-trading venues. By delivering low-latency, scalable and secure connectivity, TransFICC resolves the issues of market fragmentation, market data throughput, and increased regulation. 

TransFICC does three things: 

- It translates Execution Venue API’s to a single API. Clients connect once to TransFICC's unified API, and TransFICC manages connectivity with the electronic venues from that point. 
 
- It uses low-latency, scalable and secure technology, essential to keep pace with price updates and not get beaten to a trade by high frequency trading firms. 

- It provides timestamps for price and order messages. Measured in microseconds, timestamps record when data arrives at the bank or asset manager, helping to provide an audit trail, which supports Best Execution.

name: Koukoi Games

Besides its in-house project and product pipeline, c-LEcta has a strong focus on strategic cooperation with industrial partners. name: The Tab
about:
The Tab is a university news network run by people who like being first. We have teams of writers at leading universities in the US and UK, breaking stories and shooting videos that are seen around the world.

We were founded by three undergraduates at Cambridge University in 2009 as a reaction to out-of-touch student newspapers. Since then, The Tab has grown into a global movement of bold, fearless and entertaining journalists reaching millions of readers every month. 

Last year our scoops appeared in The New York Times, BuzzFeed, the BBC, and pretty much everywhere else. Reporters from those organizations call our journalists when they want to know what’s happening on the ground. 

Our local teams are run by student editors who decide what to cover and how to cover it. They are supported by people who used to do their job – our editing staff who work at The Tab’s headquarters in London and New York.

We hire our best people when they graduate, and so do some of the world’s leading media companies. Ellie Pithers, one of our first editors, is now Fashion Features Editor at British Vogue, and dozens more Tab graduates are working for companies like Reuters, VICE, the BBC, BuzzFeed and the Daily Mail. Soon Tab alumni will be running the media.

name: Alugha
about:

A unified workspace keeps file management and processes transparent, while team collaboration features ensure a swift turnaround time. This drastically reduces the costs of video localization projects and enables you to reach a broader and diverse audience with your message.

If you serve a multilingual audience and video is your means to get the message across, you can be sure we are here to help.

about:

Designed and developed by experts, the CounterCraft Cyber Deception Platform fits seamlessly into existing security strategies and delivers high-end deception for threat hunting and threat detection using controlled, highly credible synthetic environments.

CounterCraft accelerates threat detection earlier in the attack lifecycle, provides evidence of malicious activity and modus operandis and already protects leading organizations in the financial, trade and government sectors, as well as law enforcement agencies. The feature-rich CounterCraft Cyber Deception Platform delivers high-quality alerts with zero false positives and automates cyber deception campaigns across a complete range of digital assets to strengthen overall security posture.

The WASTX Plastic of Biofabrik White Refinery produces valuable recycling oil from plastic waste. The economic efficiency of the plant allows it to be operated profitably even with small quantities, and decentrally at the location where the waste is produced. The pyrolysis oil can be sold to the petrochemical industry or converted into electricity.

The biorefinery of Biofabrik Green Refinery extracts raw materials for the animal feed, chemical and food processing industries out of fresh grass. For these commodities can be produced in a sustainable manner fertilizer, feed and biodegradable plastics.

name: Bluepath
about:
bluepath started as a state of the art indoor positioning & navigation technology company providing location based services on iOS and Android mobile platforms. This helps and enabled our clients, partners and technology alliances to extend all the advantages of the GPS-based solutions in indoor environments. The unique approach of bluepath allows every business vertical and business model to take advantage of our technology. 

bluepath delivers an high accuracy and reliable IPS (Indoor Positioning System) technology using an unobtrusive, green and low cost Beacon infrastructure that can be easily deployed and maintained within any environment with different purposes, moving environments like trains and airplanes and outside areas which are meant to be static. The unique and innovative algorithm behind the bluepath technology uses advanced techniques of artificial intelligence to receive, categorise and analyse signals to calculate the user’s position in a closed and predefined environment. It allows to localise people, objects and assets with a precision up to maximum 1 meter. 

bluepath has been founded in 2015 and has been running as an entity out of UK and with a branch office in the UAE. In mid of 2016 the founding team of bluepath decided to move the global headquarters to Munich, Germany to be able to further develop our innovative solutions and services for our global clients in the heart of Europe. 

During the past almost 18 months our clients, partners and technology alliances have given us a great opportunity to enhance our solutions further in addition to the core of our IPS development and unique algorithm approach. 

The bluepath team is extremely excited to be in the position to provide additional unique services in the near future to enable the platform, applications and usability of IPS solutions for our clients.

name: Signal Cruncher GmbH
about:
Founded in Berlin in 2016, we develop and distribute real-time analysis systems with a focus on Smart Building, Smart Energy and Smart Factory.

With XONBOT we offer a revolutionary product for automated decision making. It enables devices and services to independently learn a optimal behavior from the interaction with the environment. Optimal means they can maximize / minimize a target size. Examples include minimizing energy consumption in the smart home or minimizing machine downtime in the industry.

Intelligent solution for networked devices and manufacturing

Our product XONBOT is an integrated and universal system for real-time analysis and decisions. It was originally developed for the retail sector to maximize customer value for merchants in real time by automating marketing actions. But beyond that, there are more uses. Due to the increasing networking of all devices ("Internet of Things"), XONBOT is useful across all industries, where decisions have to be made autonomously and self-learning.

What you can expect from XONBOT:

- compactness
- Real-time capability
- Long-term optimization
- High analytical quality

Applications:

- Smart Building
- Smart Energy
- Smart Factory

Would you like to get to know us or find out how XONBOT can help you? Then we look forward to hearing from you at info@signal-cruncher.com

Signal Cruncher
[Embedded Realtime Analytics]


https://signal-cruncher.com/legal-disclosure/

name: IAMIP
about:
IamIP has digitalized one of the last few paper-based and manually handled industries, the complex intellectual property industry. This industry is plagued by complexity with over 2.7 M new patents filed every year (growing), and $20Bn+ is lost in double work in R&D in Europe alone. IamIP’s platform enables technology based companies to easily overview and evaluate their intellectual property portfolios, monitor competition and get valuable strategic insights – in time - for determining decision-making in innovation.

Trusted by the world’s most innovative companies, IamIP’s Intellectual Property platform provides a secure, web-based portal for centrally managing all published patents worldwide – from the published individual patents to setting up search alerts, sharing, commenting, monitoring, collaborating and more. With robust analytics, IP departments and business units can make informed strategic decisions about what, where and when to take important action; i.e. filing a patent application opposition, acquire a company or technology, or to develop a new technology with a thorough understanding of financial implications of such decisions, their potential risks and opportunities for maximizing value in intellectual property. 

By using innovative big data functionality IamIP has successfully developed ground-breaking visualization possibilities of patent data that will provide you with strategic actionable insights in one single click. The IamIP platform is the most user-friendly platform on the market, where you can share documents and tasks with colleagues, request feedback including automatic reminders, saved communication history and much more - all in one click.  Say goodbye to xls files and emails; with IamIP you and your colleagues will have everything in one place.

name: Koatum
about:

Technology provides opportunity to coat any materials which could not be coated with plasma sputtering due to the high temperatures involved. An inert first layer is ensuring perfect formation between implant and coating. Upper layers, made from hydroxyapatite without the intense heat used in plasma coating, remain bioactive and durable. 

Technology also provides the ability to implement drug delivery systems. With Koatum technology surgeon can design a customised coating solution tailored to the patient’s needs.

Our range of products include:

Customers all over the world can choose from a wide selection of sailing yachts, motor yachts, catamarans and gulets all rentable with or without experienced skippers and hostesses. 

Antlos was founded with the purpose of building a network within the skipper and travellers communities, making it the first-choice platform for sailing holidays offered by private owners.

The company became part of Sailogy Group at the beginning of 2018. This deal allowed the two brands to offer a much broader and more complete service, in order to satisfy the needs of a continuously growing market.

Sailogy Group is also chosen as preferred distribution partner by professional charter companies around the World.

Nowadays, Antlos’ platform is a specialized provider of daily yacht charters, offered with or without skipper directly by companies and private boat owners. Antlos is connected in real time with a multitude of boat operators in the Mediterranean Sea and it aims to offer its customers a seamless booking process for boat experiences.

Bicedeep committed to discover the areas that AI can behave as a team member with human experts on same fields and release the solutions as state of art services.

name: Fotokite
about:
Our team believes in a future where autonomous robotics are used in meaningful, accountable applications.
Commercial UAVs have the technical capabilities to help save lives and share important stories- but they
have continued to be held back by fundamental problems in safety, regulation, and flight time. By solving these
fundamental issues, our team is able to offer the next generation of accountable and autonomous aerial robotics
that are ready for real-world use today.

Fotokite technology uses a tether combined with an onboard IMU to compute the vehicle's position relative to the user. This allows for quick deployment and controlled flight by virtually anyone and obviates the need for complex start-up protocols, GPS dependency, trained pilots, and bulky remote controls.

The core algorithms were developed and refined over the course of years of research and experimentation at the world renowned Institute for Dynamic Systems and Control at ETH Zurich. With this foundation in place, the team is now working on expanding control capabilities with a keen eye on delivering intuitive user interaction, enabling expanded capabilities to teams in Firefighting and Public Safety applications.

about:

With choices between fully loaded enterprise solution for an end to end experience or lighter more scaled down version as per the customers'fleet sizes, we are the pioneer TMS solution provider for road hauliers in all the sectors
.  
We use mobile technology, vehicle telematics and custom business solutions to connect your people to information and business processes, bringing control to commotion and helping you to work smarter.

The name ‘Proteo’ is derived from the Greek sea God Proteus who could ‘transform’ and the adjective ‘protean’ meaning flexible, versatile, adaptable. Our company name reflects what we do - we don’t implement IT solutions, we transform businesses. 
 
We provide on-going superior support to our clients' and our quality services are tailored to the individual needs of each customer. We solve clients business problems as much as we design and deliver the technology solution.
 
We have developed interchangeable technologies that provide limitless potential in the form of smarter working solutions for the management of movement. This adds value to company operations by increasing mobility and flexibility whilst empowering people with technology that makes things easier.
 
We have enormous experience in all things IT, combined with specific experience in Transport & Logistics.
We really excel in the kinds of challenging IT environments that involve distributed people or assets, remote locations and high volumes of transactions.

about:

And even though we’re a part of Google and enjoy all of the corporate perks, it still feels like you’re working at a startup.

about:

As a result, the risk of operational irregularities and potential misdiagnoses are significantly reduced and the patient safety – especially in cancer diagnostics – is greatly improved.

Since it's foundation, inveox has won a variety of awards including the 2017 "Startup des Jahres," Top 50 Start-ups 2017 from Für Gründer, the "Golden Pretzel" at Bits & Pretzels 2018 and the 2019 EIT Health Award.

name: Claimtech Inc
about:
ClaimTECH Solutions delivers a unique and critical service by bridging the gap between insurance providers and hospitals to settle 3rd Party MVA Claims without the need for time consuming and expensive litigation.

Hospitals with Trauma centers see many MVA patients. A large portion of these claims involve third party claimants. The lack of ability to properly identify the responsible party throws the hospital into the precarious position of having to file a lien on the claim to ensure getting paid upon resolution of the claim. These cases often get protracted for various reasons and the claim can often reside on the hospital's accounts receivables for months, sometimes much longer. When the hospital finally does get reimbursed, it is often at a substantially lower figure than the original bill. So after months of waiting, the payment received is very small.

Meanwhile, the auto insurance company is notified by their insured, the injured claimant or a plaintiff attorney, that there has been a medical claim generated as a result of an accident. The insurance company is then compelled to perform its due diligence to determine if the party claiming damages is in fact entitled to any payments. With the dialogue impaired by compliance with HIPAA and the intervention of a plaintiff attorney or threat of same, these bills become difficult to address and resolve.

ClaimTECH facilitates a connection directly between the hospital and the auto insurance company using a HIPAA compliant cloud based portal for claims to be settled in a fraction of the time, creating improved savings and cash flow for all parties. When a claim is settled with ClaimTECH it is settled for good, regardless of outside influences.

The company’s culture prioritizes passion, innovation, team spirit, and client satisfaction. Together, these values fuel LogPoint’s success across cybersecurity technologies: from SIEM, UEBA, and SOAR, to SAP security and protection for other business-critical applications.

about: Lifestyle and wellbeing is at the core of every human's health, happiness and productivity. A seamless, educational and engaging experience. name: Metronom Health
about:
Metronom Health is an early stage medical device company, focusing on developing an innovative, opto-enzymatic continuous blood glucose monitoring technology, for people living with diabetes.  Metronom's proprietary technology is believed to provide very significant improvements over available Continuous Glucose monitoring technologies, in terms of accuracy in the hypo-glycemic range, reliability, user friendliness, at a price for the user amenable to a broader adoption and easier coverage. 

Metromom Health was founded in 2010, and has since successfully developped a human grade commercial prototype of its system, and completed a First in Human study confirming the performance of the technology. The company is now at  a turning point of its short history, combining its focus on engineering and R&D to the development of a product that will be solidly achored into responding to the needs of the users, as well as the people caring for them. The company was founded in Laguna Hills, California.

name: AirDog
about:
We build smart robots that bring unprecedented value to its owners. 

In 2014 we set out to disrupt the way sports enthusiasts and pros capture themselves in action, and in turn, we created a completely new product category - self-flying drones. We believe that the best technology is the one that stays unnoticed. We know how important it is to stay in the moment and so we built a drone that does not require any skills to fly it.

Today we are taking it beyond video capture in sports, we believe in future where smart robots enhance our everyday life.

name: Mos
about: At Mos, we believe higher education should be a right—not a privilege.   Mos replaced the confusing, one-size-fits-none financial aid process with an intuitive application that gets students the money they need for college. Students who use Mos find an average of $15,000 in aid per year.  How is that possible? Mos is a single application for all $135B in federal and state financial aid. Mos simplifies and submits FAFSA® for students and also applies students to every state grant and scholarship for which they qualify.   Mos takes just 20 minutes but the benefits of an affordable and enriching college education last a lifetime.

name: Anvajo
about:
Anvajo GmbH, a spin-off diagnostic company from Dresden University of Technology, is a developer and manufacturer of point-of-care solutions for the diagnostic testing of liquids. After six years of research, the anvajo team has developed a portable device for point-of-care fluid analysis that has the potential to be used in a wide variety of industries.

The anvajo "fluidlab" combines two central laboratory technologies: 1. Spectroscopy and 2. Microscopy in one portable diagnostic device. The performance of each test is supported by a customly designed sample carrier system that functions in processing and delivering the fluid to the analyzer.

The fluidlab system is highly applicable in all fields of science and has many uses in human and veterinary medicine, food and feed analysis and environmental and water analysis. In veterinary and human medicine, for example, the device can be used to carry out quick diagnostic testing of blood, urine and/or sperm instantly at the point-of-need.

name: CASHLINK
about:
Cashlink is a financial technology company (fintech) in the field of digital securities founded in 2016 by Michael Duttlinger, Lars Olsson, Jonas Haag and Niklas Baumstark. The company is located at the Deutsche Börse FinTech Hub in Frankfurt am Main. The innovative team has one goal in mind: the digitalization of transferable company participation rights. It is supported by renowned investors such as the listed VC Finlab AG.

With its blockchain-based infrastructure, Cashlink enables the issuing of digital securities. For professional investors, the company creates flexible, easily transferable corporate shares regulated under German law in the form of a profit participation right. For this purpose, Cashlink cooperates with numerous partners such as the internationally renowned law firm Ashurst. Cashlink is a founding member of the International Token Standardization Association, the European forum "International Association for Trusted Blockchain Applications" (INATBA) as well as the Hesse regional group of the national German Blockchain association.

Videum is disrupting how audiences engage with health information around the world. Its mission is to aggregate, curate and share evidence-based health videos on a global scale, in any language, to empower the digital health age.

Videum's objective is to address this challenge by offering a platform for healthcare providers to reach HCPs and patients with relevant videos in their native language across all devices and a technology, which enriches videos with contextual interactive features providing for an unprecedented engagement solution.

name: Jaano
about:
At Jaano we believe that urban mobility should be easy, flexible, and cost effective. We seek to offer our customers a cheap, competitive and more adaptable transportation alternative to what is currently available. With our fleet of scooters Jaano customers will no longer have to rely on static transportation lines and will have more flexibility getting around town; at 70 cm (27.6 Inches) wide, there is no longer a need to hunt for parking, and traffic can be a thing of the past. 

After registration, Jaano customers are able to reserve and rent any available Scooter within the cities Jaano operates, direct on the Jaano app. Included with each scooter are two universally sized helmets able to fit every size of head, a universal smartphone dock to be used with navigation apps, and charging cables that will fit the majority of smartphones currently on the market. 

When the customer is ready to end their booking they only need to park the scooter within the business area, return the helmets and keys to their compartments, and end the booking on the app.
********

Weiter muss der Kunde keinen Parkplatz suchen und steht nicht im Stau.

CASHBOARD is recognized as one of the 9 top wealth tech companies in Europe (2017) and one of the market-leading companies in Germany (Aixigo/Springer 2016). The company is based in Berlin and has raised €5m to date by top-tier international VC’s including 500 Startups, Earlybird, Digital Space Ventures, Redalpine, ProSiebenSat.1 and more.

Transfection is a challenge!? Transfection is a powerful method to introduce foreign DNA or RNA into eukaryotic cells. Delivery of nucleic acids into cells enables exploration of gene function and regulation, analysis of cellular pathways and signal transduction in cells, tissues and organisms. There are various transfection techniques developed: viral transduction, mechanical methods (such as electroporation or microinjection), chemical methods (such as calcium phosphate, polymers or lipofection) and hybrid methods (such as magnetofection). Nevertheless, a successful transfection of certain cells remains a challenging task. Lipocalyx develops and manufactures the new generation proprietary synthetic transfection reagents Viromer® based on high-tech polymers that combine the best features of chemical transfection and mimick the natural uptake of the influenza virus to enable an outstanding transfer of RNAs and DNA into various hard-to-transfect cells, including primary cells, stem cells or suspension cells. Viromer® are compatible as well with many classical immortalized cell lines, including cancer cell lines widely used in cell biology. They are highly efficient, easy to use and low-toxic transfection reagents. Our company proposes a range of five color-coded Viromer® with some differences in their structural chemistry but following the same workflow. Altogether, they are addressing all of common and more specific transfection uses: mRNA and plasmid transfection, RNA-interference technology and HTS - Kits for RNAi Screening. Viromer® RED   YELLOW are optimized for plasmid / mRNA transfection gene expression by using common plasmid or highly efficient mRNA transfection, even in hard-to-transfect cells Viromer® BLUE   GREEN are optimized for siRNA / miRNA transfection from down-regulation to silencing of genes by using siRNA, as well as stimulation of gene expression through miRNA transfection, even in very challenging cells Viromer® BLACK is optimized for siRNA / anti-miR transfection a premium reagent for extremely challenging cells and with excellent performance for transfecting single-stranded antagomiRs or antisense oligonucleotides How to choose? Lipocalyx provides and updates tables on the cell specificity. For cells not described in there, we offer ready-to-use positive controls for easy testing. You just need to rehydrate the samples and put it in the media to your cells. What is transfection? The technique can be used to express exogenous nucleic acids (DNA or RNA) in other cells. Plasmid DNA (pDNA) transfection is often the method of choice, lending itself to an array of gene expression or editing studies, by inserting the DNA of interest into the hosts nucleus where it is transcribed. While DNA may be more popular, using RNA opens up exploration of protein down-regulation with RNA interference (RNAi), or blocking microRNA (miRNA) activity, without the worry of modifying the hosts genome. Transfection using mRNA tends to be more efficient than DNA, but the transfected cells tend to produce less protein due to the limited lifespan of mRNA. These different approaches can be used to generate stable, or transient transfections, depending on your needs. Cells that have been transiently transfected express the exogenous gene without incorporating it into the genome. This means that the cells will not continue to express the gene of interest through subsequent replications. Transient transfection will persist for just a few days, after which the exogenous gene is lost through mitosis or degradation. If long-term exogenous gene expression is required, stable transfection methods can be employed to generate a permanent cell line. Cells are first transfected transiently with the gene of interest, and then co-transfected with a marker gene. A marker gene that offers a selectable advantage, such as resistance to an antibiotic or toxin, is typically used. So after transient transfection the stable method works by adding the antibiotic/toxin to the cell culture. It becomes easy to identify only those that have integrated the marker gene and in all likelihood the gene of interest, into their genomes. Viral transfection This stable method is known as transduction and uses a virus carrier for the delivery of exogenous genes or probes. The viral vectors are selected based upon the specific application, but usually fall into one of four categories. Adenoviruses: double-stranded DNA viruses primarily used for transient transfection and limited to 8 kb of insert in dividing and non-dividing cells. Adeno-associated viruses: single-stranded DNA viruses that are used for stable transfection and integrate at a specific chromosomal site in dividing and non-dividing cells. These have a limited packaging capacity at just a 5 kb insert. Retroviruses: viruses with RNA genomes capable of randomly inserting double-stranded DNA copies of their genome into the chromosomes of dividing cells. They are used in stable expression experiments and can carry genetic material up to 8 kb. Lentiviruses: a type of retrovirus capable of being used in both dividing and non-dividing cells for stable transfection with up to 9 kb of insert. Viral transfection has a very high gene delivery efficiency (95100%), is a relatively simple procedure and can be used in both in vivo and in vitro settings. Mechanical transfection These methods deliver nucleic acids to a host cell by physically manipulating the cell. Electroporation for example, is a widely used and highly efficient transfection technique. It works by exposing the cells to an electric field in order to cause a temporary destabilization of the cell membrane in the form of tiny holes known as electropores. While the electric field is applied, nucleic acids can move through these pores. When the field is switched off, the pores close, leaving the exogenous nucleic acids inside the host cell. This is a simple transfection method that can be applied to a range of cell types, but is prone to high cell mortality unless correctly implemented. Alternatively, microinjection can transfect the nucleic acids directly into the nucleus of the host cell. However, this process is both time-consuming as technically demanding. Chemical transfection methods Chemical transfection can be one of the most cost-effective options. These include the use of reagents such as DEAE-dextran, calcium phosphate, cationic polymers or lipids (lipofection). Chemical methods of transfection take advantage of the well-defined chemistry of nucleic acids to either generate a precipitate that host cells will take up or that can be encouraged to fuse with and cross the cell membrane. These techniques are usually inexpensive, efficient and versatile. Their limitations come in the form of sensitivity to parameters such as pH and possible inconsistencies between reagents. Hybrid transfection methods Finally, there are hybrid or particle-based methods such as magnetofection or biolistic transfection. Magnetofection, uses a magnetic force to drive nanoparticles that have been associated with the exogenous nucleic acids into the host cell. This is rapid and has a high efficiency, yet remains a relatively new technology that requires adherent or immobilized cells. Biolistic particle transfection is similar but instead of a magnetic force, it fires nucleic acid-coated micro-particles at a high velocity through the host cell membranes. Regardless of the technique used, there are still a number of points to consider when attempting to transfect cells with either DNA or RNA. Purity, cell viability and protocol optimization all need to be controlled in order to maximize the transfection efficiency. + Read more - Read less Payment Methods Follow us Logistics Partners Lipocalyx International More Information about distributors Address Lipocalyx GmbH Weinbergweg 23 06120 Halle (Saale) Germany +49 345 555 98 36 +49 345 555 98 46 info@lipocalyx.de Imprint Payment Methods Shipping   Charges Terms   Conditions Privacy Policy Contact

name: Adsquare
about:
Adsquare is a global audience & location intelligence company helping marketers understand consumers by connecting their digital and physical worlds. As such, Adsquare is leveraging audience and location data to reveal consumer behavior. These insights enable businesses to better target and engage with their audiences and to measure their marketing effectiveness.

Using Adsquare’s independent platform solution, companies can access various data dimensions and apply them in 40 countries worldwide. 

Founded in 2012 by Tom Laband (CEO), Sebastian Doerfel (COO) and Fritz Richter (CTO) Adsquare is headquartered in Berlin, with additional offices in New York, London, Paris, Milan, Madrid, Singapore, Dusseldorf and Sydney.

For more information visit http://www.adsquare.com or contact us via info@adsquare.com.

name: DNAFit
about:
DNAfit is revolutionising the way we think about health, fitness and nutrition. We reveal the power of personal genetics to help everyone unlock their human potential, on the most personalised level possible.

Taken at home (or anywhere), our simple saliva is an easy way to discover your health, fitness and nutrigenetic profile, using the very latest in genetic technology and research – opening up a new world of truly personalised workouts, meal plans and wellbeing, whatever your goal.

As the leading global consumer brand for fitness and nutrigenetics, our reach is underpinned by a network of qualified fitness and nutrition professionals, independent and major gym chains, international distributors and professional sports clubs. From our base in London, UK, we’re changing the industry one sample at a time. 

In April 2018, DNAfit were acquired by Prenetics to become part of the Prenetics Group. Prenetics are a leading genetic testing/digital health company headquartered in Hong Kong and London, with offices in 10 countries globally. With over US $50m in strategic investments from Alibaba and Ping An, Prenetics is one of the fastest growing genetic testing and digital health groups globally.

Empower your employees to manage their own health with personalised guidance from DNAfit. For more information, please visit: https://www.dnafit.com/enterprise/

about:
In response to the increasing challenge facing the healthcare sector, a group of renowned scientists, medical doctors, entrepreneurs and academic figures is launching a unique endeavour: healthbank.

At healthbank we are building the world’s first people-owned health data transaction platform. healthbank will connect data sources from all facets of the healthcare ecosystem and reward participants for sharing their data for research purposes.  Based in Switzerland, healthbank will leverage the advantages of Swiss neutrality, trust, and data privacy to enable users, researchers, and organisations with large data sets, to unlock the value of health and medical data on our independent, global transaction platform.

healthbank is organised as a Swiss Cooperative that is fully owned and governed by its members. Its purpose is to empower users to store, access, manage and share and gain returns from their personal health information according to their needs.

Our vision is to play an active role in raising people’s awareness of health beyond illness, by providing self-governed, user-centric participative platforms and value-added services that enable health data accessibility, protection and rewards.

name: Sesam
about:
WHY?
We are experienced and committed data enthusiasts. From our point-of-view it is essential that a business possesses high quality data that they can use independent of others. Data must be put to use. Data must be protected. That is why we help businesses with what we call “democratizing data” – acquiring them access to their own data, in an adequate quality, as well as gaining the control of the data that their users – and legislators – demand.  

HOW?
Sesam offers a stand-alone, generic data platform component – a master data hub that continuously exchanges data with the business’ core systems. Every update is automatically made throughout all connected systems, providing the platform with the high-quality data needed for the business’ automated solutions. The hub requires no modifications and can also be expanded gradually. This makes Sesam the most agile and effective way to make a business truly data driven. Sesam is a SaaS application, with service and support always available.  

WHAT?
Data platforms are only as good as the processed data allows them to be. Sesam delivers a unique platform component that ensures continuous optimal data quality. This makes it easier to build cost-effective, value-increasing solutions based on the platform and quickly achieve return on investment. The component is central to a business’ ability to make use of the data platform – and essentially to a business’ ability to utilize its own data and become genuinely data-driven.

name: pritidenta GmbH
about:
Willkommen in unserer Welt!
Die Anfänge der Vollkeramik liegen über 100 Jahre zurück; um 1900 erfand ein US-amerikanischer Zahnarzt die Jacketkrone. In den 1920er Jahren wurde die Technik in Europa populär, trotz komplizierter und problembehafteter Anwendung. Als Ende der 1980er Jahre die CAD/CAM-Technologie Einzug in die Zahnheilkunde hielt, war der Grundstein für den standardmäßigen Einsatz der Vollkeramik gelegt. Heute stehen diverse Materialien zur Verfügung. Das größte Potenzial hat dabei Zirkoniumdioxid gezeigt.

Bei pritidenta dreht sich alles um diesen Werkstoff – hier liegt unsere Kernkompetenz, das ist unsere Leidenschaft. Wir machen diese eine Sache und die machen wir richtig gut. Dafür sorgen u.a. eine interne Forschung & Entwicklung und eine hauseigene Fertigung, beides am Standort Deutschland – und natürlich ein tolles Team.

Leitsatz der pritidenta
Wir entwickeln Produkte für Dentaltechniker und Zahnärzte, die hohe Ästhetik mit der effizienten Herstellung und Automatisierung im CAD/CAM Bereich kombiniert. Ziel ist es unseren Kunden eine hochwertige Lösung zu einem fairen Preisleistungsverhältnis anzubieten.

name: BECOM Systems
about:
We make machines perceive their environment like never before by providing 3D depth sensors for the industrial market.

Since its foundation BECOM Systems has been synonymous with optimized embedded systems and sensor solutions of highest quality. BECOM Systems is regarded as an expert in 3D ToF (Time of Flight) Depth Sensing sensor solution. Its extensive experience and know-how in embedded system design is used for a broad spectrum of products. The development of customer specific solutions completes the offered services.

Products
Its products include ToF based depth sensors and DSP as well as ARM based SoMs (System on Modules). 

Solutions
Building on top of BECOM Systems' own range of embedded hardware platforms, we develop customer specific embedded systems in a fast and efficient way.

Laboratories
BECOM Systems’ accredited in-house EMC laboratory in Vienna offers various Electromagnetic Compatibility (EMC) services including development support.

History
BECOM Systems started its business in 2004 - under the name "BLUETECHNIX" - with System on Modules (SoM) based on the Blackfin DSP (digital signal processor) form Analog Devices and became the world market leader for these kind of SoMs. In addition BECOM Systems did embedded system designs for several international companies. 

Beginning in 2011 BECOM Systems made a bootstrapped transition to become the supplier for ToF (time of flight) based depth sensors for the industrial market.

name: novaliq gmbh
about:
Novaliq is a pharmaceutical company focusing on the development and commercialization of first- and best-in-class ocular therapeutics based on EyeSol®, the first water-free technology worldwide for ophthalmology products. With an initial focus on dry eye disease (DED), Novaliq offers an industry-leading portfolio addressing today’s unmet medical needs of millions of patients with eye disease. 

With an initial focus on dry eye disease (DED), Novaliq offers an industry-leading portfolio addressing today’s unmet medical needs of millions of patients with eye disease. 

NOV03 and CyclASol® are the two late stage development compounds. NOV03 is the first drug developed to treat evaporative DED associated with meibomian gland dysfunction in a highly effective way. CyclASol®, an ophthalmic solution of 0.1% cyclosporine A in EyeSol®, is an anti-inflammatory and immunomodulating drug for the treatment of aqueous deficient DED. Both compounds have shown superior clinical benefit, with an onset of action and an excellent tolerability profile.  

NovaTears® water-free eye drops for dry eye disease have CE certification and are commercialized in Australia/New Zealand by AFT Pharmaceuticals and in Europe as EvoTears® by Ursapharm. Novaliq is headquartered in Heidelberg, Germany and has an office in Cambridge, MA, USA. 

The long-term shareholder is dievini Hopp BioTech Holding, an active investor in Life and Health Sciences companies.

name: ProVita
about: NMC ProVita International Medical Center, a subsidiary of the UAE's largest private healthcare provider NMC Healthcare, is the pioneer for post-acute care (including long-term care, inpatient and outpatient rehabilitation, and home health services) in the Middle East.  NMC ProVita specializes in the treatment and management of non-acutely ill patients of all ages requiring premium personalized healthcare services in a comfortable and compassionate setting. NMC ProVita employs a team of specialized physicians, nurses and therapists who focus on improving patientsâ quality of life with cutting edge medical solutions and customized treatment programs.  Established in 2011, NMC ProVita manages 2 multidisciplinary therapy outpatient departments and a total of almost 280 post-acute care beds at designated facilities in Abu Dhabi, Al Ain, Dubai and Muscat, Oman as well as private units at NMC Royal Hospital Abu Dhabi and Al Zahra Hospital Sharjah to address all inpatient and outpatient post-acute care needs across the region.  NMC ProVita also manages the skilled nursing, medical, rehabilitation and dialysis needs of almost 300 patients in the comfort of their homes throughout the UAE as the operator of Americare Home Health Services, Taskeen, Premiere, Reaya and Emirates Rehabilitation &.  NMC ProVita was the first long-term care rehabilitation facility in the region to attain the prestigious Joint Commission International Accreditation in 2013. name: Seerene
about:
Seerene is the first integrated Digital Engineering Platform for the end-to-end management of software systems. 

Seerene's software analytics platform provides actionable insights into software development processes, source code, system evolution, and software developers. Seerene, using AI, extracts the meta data and analyses it holistically and with respect to various issues in software development, such as for risk prevention, effort estimation, team composition, etc. The analytics platform incorporates all phases of the software development process and software delivery (end-to-end). By leveraging AI to integrate all available data from tools, methods, and metrics, Seerene creates a new foundation of shared knowledge and insights in the form of their ‘Digital Boardroom’, empowering the decision-markers in software engineering.

The Seerene Digital Boardroom becomes the central reporting, control, and management system, with which the various factors in software development are optimally aligned with company goals and objectives. Seerene's SaaS-based analytics platform works independent of the programming languages, software methodology, software technologies, and software frameworks. The platform uses AI and machine learning to analyze complex relationships that occur during software development.

Sereene has offices in Potsdam and Berlin. The startup started as the offspring of fifteen years of research at the Hasso Plattner Institute.  Seerene is funded by Lakestar and Earlybird, two of the most prominent VCs in Europe. In 2016, it won the Digital Top 50 ‘Best Startup’ award from Google and McKinsey & Company. In 2018, Seerene was placed in the Microsoft Scaleup program for the most innovative postseries A startups in Europe.

name: Celltool
about:
* CellTool – Raman laser microscopy:  Single cell analysis- live cell laser trapping- label free- non destructive – digital microscopy - tissue and cell suspension - Metabolomic Fingerprint. 
* CellTool combines two Nobel Prize winning technologies in one system. 

Raman laser excites cellular components like DNA, proteins, lipids, sugars to produce a characteristic photonic spectrum that is specific for cell type and status. This offers many fields of application in precision medicine.
• Cancer research: e.g. Cancer- non cancer classification, tumors aggressiveness, treatment response, spheroids, organoids.
• Stem cell research: e.g. Cell differentiation, homogeneity, activation, contamination.
• Regenerative medicine: e.g. 3D cell cultures, cells growth on scaffolds, cells transfection rate.
• QC of cell therapeutic products: e.g. Skin grafts, blood bags, contaminations, immune cells activation. 
• Microbiology: e.g. Identification of bacterial species, fungi, yeast, other microorganisms.
• Cell biology: e.g. Basic research, systems biology, live cells, single cell sorting.

Our flagship product BioRam® is specifically designed for biologists and physicians and easy to use. It consists of an inverted digital microscopic platform equipped with:
• Confocal Raman microscopic setup.
• Motorized scanning stage.
• Integrated (Laser) Optical Trap and sorting
• Cell culture incubator (live cells measurements)
• Confocal fluorescence configurations 
• Measurement software that is highly optimized for rapid data acquisition 
• Automatic data analysis software.

The tool is applicable across numerous use cases with directly measurable success in sales & marketing, compliance, risk & fraud, research, and data management. It enables companies to recognize the value of their network and to expand that value through better-informed decisions and actions. The name Palturai was inspired by the Hungarian mathematician Pál Turán, a co-founder of graph theory.

Durch die Automatisierung des Beratungsprozesses spart der Kunde Zeit und Ressourcen. Auf Seiten von dayzzi ermöglicht es eine effizientere und damit kostengünstigere Abwicklung. So sparen Kunden gleicht doppelt. 

Dayzzi führt nur die besten Werbeartikel. Wir sehen uns als Boutique für Werbeartikel, die durch Qualität besticht. Dazu gehört auch der Service. Durch langjährige Erfahrung auf dem Gebiet und Leidenschaft für die Produkte und Branche beraten unsere Mitarbeiter kompetent und kundenorientiert. Somit verzichten Kunden trotz Technik nicht auf persönlichen Service – wenn nötig.

name: Sonovum
about:
Sonovum entwickelt zukunftsweisende Technologien

Sonovum vereint die Expertise von Akustocerebrografie (ACG), Mathematik, Statistik, Medizintechnik und Medizin. Die Mitarbeiter bringen umfangreiche Erfahrung in Forschung und Produktentwicklung sowie fachärztliche Expertise etwa aus der Neurologie und der Intensivmedizin ein, um die Technologie kontinuierlich weiterzuentwickeln.

In den kommenden Jahren wird das Anwendungsspektrum der ACG- Technologie in den Bereichen Diagnostik, Monitoring und Therapieüberwachung stetig erweitert. Darüber hinaus wird die Integration in klinische Monitoring- und Auswertesysteme vorangetrieben. Die Entwicklung von Apps und telemedizinischen Workflows befindet sich in der Vorbereitung, um den Mehrwert für Patienten und Anwender zusätzlich zu steigern.

name: Fintura
about:
Smart finanzieren - so einfach wie noch nie!

Wir verhelfen kleinen und mittelständischen Unternehmen, Freiberuflern und Selbstständigen zu Finanzierungen von Maschinen, Fuhrpark, Betriebsmitteln und Gewerbeimmobilien. Dadurch erhalten unsere Kunden die Möglichkeit in Wachstum zu investieren, Liquidität zu erhalten und finanzielle Mittel zu beschaffen.

Unser Team unterstützt Sie über den gesamten Prozess und bringt Sie mit ihrem ausgewählten Finanzierungspartner zusammen.

Sie nutzen Fintura kostenfrei. Wir finanzieren uns durch eine einheitliche Erfolgsprovision von der Bank. Weil die Provision bei allen Banken gleich ist, stellen wir sicher, dass wir keine Bank bevorzugen und nur Ihre Interessen vertreten.

Wir finden die passende Finanzierung
und den passenden Finanzierungspartner

Sie können sich ganz auf Ihr Geschäft fokussieren, während wir uns um Ihre beste Finanzierung kümmern! Unser Online-Konditionen-Vergleich verschafft Ihnen Transparenz. Mit unserer Expertise und schlanken Prozessen sparen Sie wertvolle Zeit und kommen direkt ans Ziel.

Wir schaffen Gestaltungsfreiraum und Unabhängigkeit in finanziellen Belangen wie z.B. Kredite, Leasing, Mietkauf, Finetrading und Factoring. Unabhängig arbeiten wir mit Banken, Leasingunternehmen, Spezialfinanzierern, FinTechs u.a. zusammen.

name: Dormando
about:
Das Start-Up Unternehmen Dormando ist der Onlineshop rund ums Thema Schlafen. Hier findest du eine riesige Auswahl an Markenprodukten aus den Bereichen Matratzen, Betten und Bettwaren für den schönsten Schlaf deines Lebens.

In einer Branche, in der das Produkt individuell zum Kunden passen muss, haben wir es uns im Herzen Frankfurts zur Aufgabe gemacht, durch einen außergewöhnlichen Service via Telefon, Email oder unserem Online Berater, die optimale Matratze für unsere Kunden zu finden und haben es dadurch geschafft der deutschlandweite Produktführer in Sachen Matratzen zu werden.

Mit Blick auf die Frankfurter Skyline arbeiten wir mit viel Einsatz für den Erfolg und den ständigen Wachstum des Unternehmens. Die außergewöhnliche Arbeitsatmosphäre motiviert die Mitarbeiter jeden Tag aufs Neue und sorgt für ein starkes Zusammengehörigkeitsgefühl. Bei Dormando stehen flache Hierarchien, Teamwork, Kreativität und Arbeitseinsatz im Vordergrund und bildet die Basis für unseren Erfolg.

name: WunderAgent
about:
Unsere übergeordnete Mission ist es, unseren Kunden die Immobilie als Anlageform näher zu bringen. Warum? Ganz einfach. Weil Deutschland im Vergleich zu anderen europäischen Ländern viel weniger Immobilieneigentümer aufweist. Dabei sind Häuser, Wohnungen und Grundstücke sehr gute Wege der Altersvorsorge und zur Generierung von passivem Einkommen - wenn man weiß wie.

Für uns steht die vertrauensvolle und nachhaltige Beratung und Begleitung unserer Kunden im Mittelpunkt. Langanhaltende Partnerschaften sind eines unserer wichtigsten Ziele. Deshalb möchten wir als Spezialisten da sein, wenn es Fragen gibt - auch nach dem erfolgreichen Ankauf der Immobilie.

Mit datengetriebenen Analysen von Objekten und Nachbarschaften sind wir in der Lage interessante Immobilien passgenau auf die Ziele unserer Kunden zu identifizieren.

Von Investoren für Investoren geschaffen, bietet WunderAgent Research, Analysen und Einblicke, um unabhängig Immobilien zu bewerten und zu erwerben - und das völlig transparent.

Wir sind mit ganzem Herzen dabei und deshalb sind Immobilien nicht nur ein Teil unsere Arbeit. Sie sind unsere Leidenschaft und der Antrieb für unsere tägliche Arbeit.

name: Quobyte
about: Quobyte turns commodity servers into a  Data Center File System. Based on latest distributed systems technology, Quobyte delivers linear scalability, full fault tolerance, and lights-out operations – so that you can focus on your business applications and stop worrying about your storage infrastructure.

name: Gastfreund
about:
Digitale Kommunikation und Betreuung der Gäste

Digitale Tools zählen heutzutage in der Hotellerie vor und nach dem Aufenthalt zum Service-Standard und sind tief in die Arbeitsprozesse verankert. Allerdings reißt die digitale Betreuung des Gastes meist bei seiner Ankunft ab. Dabei ist die Aufenthalts-Phase des Gastes entscheidend für erfolgreiche Hotels – sie ist der Schlüssel zu mehr Umsatz und glücklichen Gästen.

Daher bieten wir unseren Kunden aus der Hotellerie digitale Produkte zur Kommunikation und Betreuung ihrer Gästen vor, während und nach dem Aufenthalt an: die digitale Gästemappe, die WLAN-Willkommensseite, die eigene Hotel-App, den Online-Editor zur Erstellung einer eigenen Hotelzeitung und den Infokanal für TVs und Monitore.

Mit diesen Produkten erreicht der Hotelier seine Gäste mit Angeboten, Services und Informationen rund um deren Aufenthalt über verschiedene Kontaktpunkte – egal ob über Smartphones, Tablets, Laptops, Fernseher oder am Frühstückstisch. Setzen Sie auf digitalen Service und ergänzen Sie die persönliche Betreuung Ihrer Gäste mit digitalen Helfern!

✓ Verbessert den Gästeservice
✓ Steigert den Umsatz
✓ Entlastet die Mitarbeiter

Über 6.500 Kunden aus 15 Ländern vertrauen uns.

Weitere Informationen gibt es unter www.gastfreund.net und auf dem Gastfreund-Blog unter blog.gastfreund.net.

name: Subitec
about:
Subitec offers plants for the industrial cultivation of microalgae and cyanobacteria, as well as the necessary pre-culture and laboratory systems.
Like all plant species, microalgae and cyanobacteria grow through photosynthesis, i.e. through the presence of water, CO2, nutrients and temperature in nature.
By artificially reproducing these natural conditions, a highly productive habitat can be created.
Subitec offers systems based on proprietary technology for this purpose.

name: Parkpocket
about: › Acquired by Continental (09.2017) › Investors: Telefónica Germany, GFT Technologies  Parkpocket is an award winning smart mobility startup aggregating, processing and licensing parking information. The company´s data solution can be used via its own mobile app, but is also easily integrated into other digital devices, services and connected car solutions. Thus, parkpocket addresses customers in industries such as automotive, navigation, ICT, traveling and others.

name: VAT4U
about:
Every year more than 10 billion Euros are lost by companies since they are not recovering Value Added Tax on their foreign expenses…

VAT4U simplifies your travel expense management process & automates your VAT recovery – stop loosing money while travelling with Europe’s leading automated VAT refund platform.

VAT4U transforms a complex process into an easy-to-manage online solution; users can register their foreign expenses and VAT4U manages the rest.

We monitor over 2000 VAT rules in the European Union & submit your VAT claims to the relevant tax administrations.

Don’t waste money when traveling - claim your foreign VAT back with VAT4U!

name: Wine in Black
about:
Wine in Black was conceived out of passion for superb wine and a belief that quality beats quantity. Founded in 2011, Wine in Black runs an exclusive online shop for premium wines, which delights our customers with constantly updated wine-offers. In turn we are rewarded with outstanding customer loyalty. Our offer of an easy and personalized way to experience curated premium wines disrupts the European wine market and we are always searching for enthusiastic colleagues. 
Our office right in the heart of Berlin is the ideal environment for 40 clever, creative and committed employees. Not only do we offer attractive job opportunities and an international environment but also lots of first-class wine. If you also dream of a world in which all people truly enjoy wine, Wine in Black will be the right place for you!


There is no easier way to discover the best wines of the world!

name: ParkTAG
about: ParkTAG: Free Social Parking App DOWNLOAD FEATURES CITIES FAQs COMMUNITY CONTACT B2B See Which Space Vacates! Save your time, money and nerves. ParkTAG tells you about vacating parking spaces. See Which Space Vacates! Save your time, money and nerves. ParkTAG tells you about vacating parking spaces. Reviews "A very useful app ! Deserving to be known, if you live in a big city and if you spend too much time searching for a parking lot :-) " Julie - Android  "Great App User friendly   helpful App, thanks!" Andreea -iOS  "A social network for parking spots." PSFK.COM "Still looking for a parking or did you already park?!" Kathleen - Android  "Very helpful app, not more too say" Juliano01 - iOS  "Great app! No more car parking tension." Adnan Khan - Android  How It Works 1. DOWNLOAD Download ParkTAG for Android or iOS 2. OPEN Open the app in one of our cities when you need a space 3. DRIVE Select and drive to the parking space of your choice 4. SHARE WITH THE COMMUNITY Let the app run in the background so that others also find the spaces you vacate No More Parking Search. Ever. ParkTAG is an easy to use application that helps you to find free parking spots in your city. It works with an auto-detection algorithm. This means that ParkTAG detects, in real time, parking spots that are available or will become available in the near future. You´ll see upcoming spots up to 10 minutes before other drivers! Unlike other applications, ParkTAG shows curbside parking spots and not just private parking. The app works via community involvement and is free of charge for your. The more users the better it becomes. Just by opening the app you are automatically contributing to the community. Check out how ParkTAG works here! ParkTAG Cities Stockholm Berlin Copenhagen Munich Oslo Hamburg Vienna More cities coming soon... Your city is missing? Tell us where you are. Well notify you when the community grows in your city. KEEP ME UPDATED So Many Questions So, yet another parking app? ParkTAG helps you find a curbside parking space. You can see where other ParkTAG users already vacated or will vacate their parking space in a few minutes. Basically ParkTAG allows you to look into the future. This works already in the above mentioned cities. Uhmsocial parking? What does that really mean? The ParkTAG community helps each other to find parking spaces. All users let the ParkTAG app run on their phone. The app automatically detects when one parked. It will automatically detect when the car vacates again. That vacating parking space will be visible to the community. Completely anonymously! What sourcery is this, sire? We use clever algorithms that understand the sensor data from your smartphone. Thus the app detects when you are about to vacate or just vacated a parking space. The vacancy will be visible anonymously to other members of the community. That´s how you help other users to find a parking spot (and vice versa). Urg...are you tracking me? No! At no point can someone identify your position. No real-time location data is ever transmitted. The algorithm works directly on your phone. Once a parking event occurs the anonymous information is transmitted. Effectively that data package contains the coordinates of the parking space (not you!), a timestamp, an event type and an identifier for the phone (not you, again!). To improve the app you can decide to turn the Training module on. This module temporarily submits some extra sensor data to us. During the training period the algorithm operates on our server. You can find more information about data security in our Terms and Conditions and the Privacy Policy. If anything is unclear to you, we are happy to receive an E-mail. Grrr, the map is emptyno vacancy around me? The more drivers join the community, the more parking spots will be visible. So when there is no vacancy around you it means that you are the first parking hero in your area. Invite friends, family and neighbors to join the community. With every member you recruit, the community grows and you have an easier life finding parking. Or please contact us via Facebook, Twitter or e-mail us and we will try to find more users in your area. Woop, woop! How can I help? Install ParkTAG. Let it run in the background. Enjoy the ride. There is no need to manually repoort anything. The app detects automatically when you are about to vacate a parking space. You can help e´verybody most, if you spread the word. The more people use ParkTAG the higher the chance that someone is vacating where you are arriving. Green, gray, pins. My head is spinning... Youll find three different pins on the map: Green Pins (<10); parking spots vacating in the next 10 minutes. Green Pins (<5); parking spots vacating in less than 5 minutes. Grey Pins (<5); are recently vacated parking spaces (less than 5 minutes). Narf, got there but no parking :( Case 1: The green pins (5 or 10 minutes) are shown on the map when a vacating space is detected. Depending on the time you drove to the parking space, it is possible that the vacancy cleared before you arrived. To avoid it, we will soon introduce a system to allow a personal handover between you and other users. Case 2: The gray pins (5 minutes) are shown on the map when someone has already vacated. If the parking spaces still available or not, depends on traffic. Please use your own judgement, if its worth trying to reach this parking space. You obviously have to consider the time of day and demand for parking spaces. Dude, I am gonna sue your ***! It might be that a driver occupies a parking space without using ParkTAG. Parking spaces are public property. Most driving regulations around the world state that a driver waiting with the indicator has the right of way. So if you´re already standing at the vacant parking space with flashing indicator, its yours. But please always be respectful. The world is competitive enough already Does ParkTAG run on indestructable Nokia 3310? ParkTAG is currently available for iPhones (5 and up) and for Android phones (4.2 and up). We have a team of 3 engineers trying to open a Nokia shell since a few months. Once we have it open we might be able to estimate development time for you. Is the app really for free? Like really, really? We are financed by the Hightech Gründerfond (public-private-partnership between the German Ministry of economics and German corporates). Also the European Commission supports us through the Horizon 2020 program. Our revenues come from car manufacturers, mobility apps on other corporates who license the technology we invented. ...more questions Hello World! This is us. We were trying to find funny pictures. But had to realize we are fairly un-funny... name: LOCLET
about:
LOCLET verbindet Menschen mit Orten auf spielerische Art und Weise.  In dem ortsbasierten Quizspiel können Spieler spannende Rätsel - so genannte “Loclets” - an Orten in der Stadt lösen und selbst platzieren. LOCLET ermöglicht somit das spielerische Entdecken und Erkunden von Städten. 

Die Smartphone-App geleitet Nutzer vor Ort zu den Rätseln. Um ein Loclet zu lösen, muss man es öffnen und sich meist in kurzer Zeit nach Hinweisen in der Umgebung  umschauen. 
Nutzer können einzelne Regionen “erobern” indem sie dort möglichst viele Rätsel lösen. Auch fremde Städte können Teil des Siegeszuges werden - dank spezieller Loclets, die von überall aus geöffnet werden können. So ersetzt  LOCLET den Reiseführer vor dem nächsten Städtetrip.

Egal, ob man eine Stadt rein virtuell oder real durchkämmt, stets sammelt der Spieler wertvolle oder lustige Gegenstände, die das Spielerlebnis erweitern und neue Fähigkeiten verleihen.  Lokale Ranglisten und Herausforderungen unter Freunden führen zu einem besonderen Spielspaß und ermöglichen den direkten Vergleich im Quizwettstreit.

Die Vorstellung Eurer Traumhochzeit ist romantisch, die Hochzeitsplanung kann jedoch schnell stressig werden. Uns von Foreverly liegt es am Herzen, dass die Planung Eures großen Tages so unkompliziert wie möglich verläuft  ganz gleich, ob Ihr einen Hochzeitsplaner nutzt oder die Hochzeitsvorbereitung selbst in die Hände nehmt. Wenn Ihr Euch darüber im klaren seid, ob Ihr eine kirchliche Trauung, standesamtliche Eheschließung oder gar eine freie Trauzeremonie feiern möchtet, solltet Ihr durch die große Auswahl an unvergesslich schönen Hochzeitslocations stöbern. Für den perfekten Brautlook findet Ihr bei uns natürlich auch Stylisten und für alle Naschkatzen auch Bäcker, die Euch die allerschönsten Hochzeitstorten zaubern. Während Bräute schnell vom Brautkleid träumen, Gäste sich schöne Hochzeitssprüche für ihre Reden aussuchen und der Bräutigam nach dem passenden Hochzeitsanzug sucht, tun unsere Dienstleister alles in ihrer Macht stehende, um perfekt auf Euren großen Tag vorbereitet zu sein. Unsere Dienstleister wissen über neue Hochzeitstrends immer zuerst Bescheid und setzen neueste Must-Haves und Inspirationen nach Eurem Geschmack um. Genau dafür stehen wir auch mit unserem Leitsatz: Foreverly -Einfach perfekt heiraten. Wir wollen, dass Eure ganz persönliche Traumhochzeit genau so abläuft, wie sie für Euch perfekt ist. about: What is Stylight?  Founded in 2008, Stylight is the leading aggregation platform for the fashion and lifestyle industry worldwide. With our technology, reach, data and market knowledge, we help our partners operate and achieve their goals. Investments in innovation and talent make us a trusted partner for premium brands and retailers all over the world for more than 10 years.  Part of ProSiebenSat.1 Media SE, Stylight is not an online store, but an inspiration and aggregation platform that allows shoppers to price compare products and proceed with their order with one easy click. More than a search engine, the Stylight online magazine offers the best in beauty, fashion, and home & living inspiration. Stylight is based in Munich, Germany, with offices in Philadelphia, USA. name: Finanzchef24
about:

Wir bieten Unternehmern und Selbstständigen in Deutschland digital Gewerbeversicherungen über unsere unabhängige Online-Vergleichsplattform an. Kern des Vergleichsrechners ist eine Risikoanalyse, die Grundlage für passgenaue Versicherungslösungen ist. Mittlerweile nutzen 46 namhafte Produktpartner wie Allianz, ARAG, ERGO, HDI, Hiscox, R+V und VHV diesen neuen Vertriebsweg. 
Unser Vergleichsrechner kann für rund 1450 verschiedene Berufe und Betriebsarten individuelle Angebote zu Betriebshaftpflicht-, Berufshaftpflicht-, Vermögensschadenhaftpflicht-, Gewerberechtsschutz-, D&O-, Cyber- und Geschäftsinhaltsversicherungen erstellen.

Wir arbeiten immer nach unserem Motto: Gewerbe einfach gut versichert.

name: European Games Group
about:
Your F2P Game Publisher

GamesGroup is a free-to-play, cross-platform browser and mobile game publisher based in Munich, Germany, with an international, dynamic team of video game industry experts. We enable independent-minded developers to scale their game successfully on a global level by providing the full range of marketing and commercial exploitation, covering all aspects in the diverse universe of global online games marketing and revenue management.

name: Manugoo
about:
manugoo ist crowdsourcing für Konsumgüter. Auf unserer Plattform hast du die Möglichkeit dich aktiv am Produktentwicklingsprozess zu beteiligen. Es können Probleme geteilt, Ideen vorgeschlagen, Meinungen abgegeben und fertige Produkte eingereicht werden. Die Crowd löst die geteilten Probleme, stimmt über die einzelnen Ideen und darauf folgenden Entwicklingsschritte ab und entscheidet welches Produkt produziert und verkauft werden soll. Dieser Prozess führt dazu, dass manugoo bereits validierte und auf dich zugeschnittene Produkte vertreibt.

Die Produkte werden über unseren Laden, unsere Onlineplattform und verschiedene Partner vertrieben. 

Wir stehen für hochwertige, innovative Produkte, welche unter fairen Bedingungen produziert werden.


manugoo is crowdsourcing for consumer goods. Products are developed with the help of the crowd. If enough feedback is given, products will be developed by us an produced by our production partners and finally distributed via our manugoo website and via our online and retail partner. User (the crowd) have the possibility to take active part in the product development process on our website www.manugoo.de.

The crowdsourcing process is divided into four parts:
1. Problems/Ideas can be shared
2. Solutions are proposed
3. Comments can be left
4. Products ready for sale are submitted

User have the opportunity to solve shared problems, vote for submitted ideas and the following process of development (function, form, colours, material, price and so on). Moreover they take on research tasks, submit complementary ideas and finally decide on which developed products will be produced and sold in the end. There is a fair compensation system for the incorporation of ideas or opinions, so that user can benefit from participation in crowdsourcing. Thanks to the crowdsourcing process manugoo is able to produce and distribute consumer goods which are validated and tailored to the particular needs of the consumer successfully.
